title: dilled cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumber and onion.
In bowl add sour cream vinegar, sugar, dill, salt and pepper.
Toss cucumbers in sour cream mixture.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Dice onions very fine.
In large pan, saute onions in butter for a few minutes.
Add soup, crabmeat, cayenne pepper and salt. Add cream and milk.
(Note:
Use milk to thin for consistency.) It should be thick to medium.
Cook over low heat until heated through.
Do not boil.

title: awesome slow-cooked chili
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Set it to high until it boils, then set crock-pot to low and cook 5 to 6 hours.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots until medium done.
Pour mixture of remaining ingredients over carrots in glass container with top. Refrigerate for at least a day ahead.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: yale beets
directions: Place beets in greased casserole dish.
Mix flour, salt and sugar together.
Combine with butter, water, orange juice and lemon juice.
Cook until thick, about 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Pour over beets and bake in oven for 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: glazed baked chicken with stuffed sweet spanish onions
directions: Place chicken in glass baking dish, skin side up.
Combine all other ingredients and brush on chicken.
Put in a 375° oven and bake for 1 hour.
Turn after 30 minutes, brushing frequently with glaze.
(Reserve some glaze for the onions.)
Garnish with parsley and lemon slices.
Serves 4.

title: bacon, cheese, tomato sandwiches
directions: Cook bacon.
On 1
slice
of
bread,
put
a
slice
of cheese.
On another, put tomato slices.
Put bacon between and put the 2 slices of bread together.
Butter the sides of bread and cook same as a grilled cheese sandwich.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Put in shallow dish, then layer remaining ingredients in order.
Serve with dip size Fritos.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt
unsweetened chocolate and cool.
Add vanilla.
Cream oleo with sugar.
Add chocolate mixture to oleo sugar mixture. Add eggs, one at a time, beating a full five minutes after each. Put in graham cracker crust.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of coloring and cocoa and add this to butter mixture.	Add everything except the vinegar and soda.
Beat. After beating, add vinegar and soda.
Mix well and pour into two layer pans that have been greased and floured bake 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: potluck potato casserole
directions: In a large bowl, defrost potatoes with 1/2 cup melted butter. Add salt, pepper, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese. Blend well. Pour into buttered casserole (3-quart).
Mix 1/2 cup melted butter with cornflake crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45
minutes.
Serves 10.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: italian dressing
directions: Mix eggs and cheese.
Add finely chopped salami to mixture. Then add bread crumbs until it is the consistency of dough.
Stuff the cavity of a 4 pound chicken and bake uncovered for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: tang pie(club member: clint hudson)
directions: Mix Tang, sour cream, milk and half of Cool Whip. Pour into pie crust. Put rest of Cool Whip on top of pie.

title: low-fat raisin-rice cereal
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Add a small amount to soft cheeses for a delicious snack.
Serve with crackers.

title: grilled vegetables
directions: *Can use eggplant, broccoli, zucchini, onion, cherry tomatoes and carrots.

title: swiss steak
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with foil.
Place steak in pan.
Add butter, onion soup and drained tomatoes on top of steak.
Shake together in a jar the soup, salt, tomato juice, A.1. sauce and cornstarch.
Pour over steak.
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 250°.

title: hamburger steak
directions: Season ground beef with salt and pepper.
Shape into 4 large patties.
Brown in large skillet.
Mix brown gravy as directed on package plus 1/2 more cup of water.
Bring to a boil.
Drain grease from the hamburger patties.
Pour gravy mixture over the meat. Slice onion thin and arrange on top of patties.
Bring to boil. Cover pan and reduce heat to a simmer.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: granny rolls
directions: Add shortening and sugar to boiling water; then let cool.
Mix yeast, warm water and eggs; stir well.
Then add flour alternately with shortening mixture.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Pour out on floured surface; knead just enough to handle easily.
Use a biscuit cutter to cut out rolls.
Dip in melted butter; then fold in half.
Let rise about 3 hours; then bake at 400° about 20 minutes.
Makes about 50 medium rolls.
They will continue to rise and bake better if started in a cold oven.

title: aunt mary's red rice
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Place all ingredients in rice steamer. Mix to coat rice.
Cook over steady steam about 45 minutes.
Do not stir during cooking process.
Serves 6.

title: sally's seven minute icing
directions: Mix in double boiler and place over boiling water.
Stir 6 minutes to about 150 strokes.
Remove from heat.
Beat with rotary beater until icing will hold its shape.
Fold in 1 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.

title: kismet biscuit(to put weight on bulldogs)
directions: The ingredients should be kneaded together so that all parts are mixed well.
Whatever your imagination may say, make it into patties, meatballs or just chunks, particularly if you are going to feed more than one dog.

title: chicken soup
directions: Lay 6 chicken breasts in pot; cover with water and add salt to taste.
Cook until it falls off bones.
Add celery seed.
Bone chicken and skin.
Reserve broth.
Put broth back in pot; add peas, carrots, whipping cream and cheese.
Add and dissolve bouillon cubes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1- 1/2 quart casserole, mix soup, milk and pepper.
Stir in beans and 2/3 cup French Fried Onions.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in 6 cups of boiling water (salted) for 12 minutes; drain, but do not rinse.
While macaroni is cooking, combine mushroom soup, evaporated milk and pimentos.
Add liquid from salmon, the salmon flaked in large chunks and 1/2 the grated cheese.
Mix well.
Heat on low heat.
Stir in macaroni.
Pour into oiled 6-cup baking dish.
Combine remaining cheese and crumbs; sprinkle over salmon and macaroni mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour and powdered sugar; cut in margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan; 1/2-inch ridge on side.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: big cookie
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Spread on pizza pan and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: washington cottage pudding *
directions: *A speedy cake that is perfect with a fruit dessert sauce spooned atop.

title: frozen raspberry cream pie
directions: Crush cookie cereal in resealable plastic bag with rolling pin. In bowl, mix cereal crumbs and margarine. Press the mixture evenly in 9-inch pie plate. Layer 3/4 cup berries over crust. Combine yogurt and Cool Whip. Gently fold in another 3/4 cup berries. Pour mixture into pie crust. Freeze for 3 hours. Garnish with leftover berries.

title: crab bisque
directions: Saute onions, celery and carrots in 1/2 cup butter until soft. Add lobster shells and white wine.
Cook until shells are red.
Add fumet, clam juice and chicken stock.
Simmer one hour.
Add rice and simmer thirty minutes longer.
Food mill rice and put through small tamis.
Bring to boil, add heavy cream and cognac.
Add saffron and season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Steam chicken 1 hour and 15 minutes in 2 cups water.
Cool and pull chicken off bone.
Cut in bite-sized pieces.
Save broth and add 2 more cups of water; bring to a boil.
Add frozen vegetables and cook until they are still a little bit crisp.
Add potatoes, tomatoes and onion.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add cabbage and chicken; cook 10 minutes longer.
Makes large portion.
May freeze.

title: rhubarb cookies
directions: Mix shortening, egg, syrup, sugar and rhubarb together.
Add all but last 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Then add coconut, raisins and nuts.
Mix well and chill. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie pan.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes in 375° oven.

title: melon ball slush
directions: Bring to boil water and sugar.
Let cool.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Freeze and serve in highball glass with sours or ginger ale to taste.

title: country apple butter
directions: Cook apples for 6 hours; add sugar.
Cook 2 more hours.
Add flavoring of your choice, cinnamon or vanilla.
I prefer cinnamon. Cook for 1 hour longer.
Fill jars and seal immediately.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini.
Coat with mixture.
Place on well sprayed (or oiled) cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip - oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Cream shortening until fluffy.
Add sugars, creaming well.
Beat in eggs.
Add water, sifted ingredients, nuts, chips and oatmeal in order listed, mixing well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Pour first 6 ingredients into a heavy 6-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Five minutes before serving, add cilantro and tortilla chips.
Serve in bowl and top with cheese, sour cream and olives.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake as directed.
Melt 1 cup Milnot, 1 cup
sugar, marshmallows and coconut together; bring to a boil. Pour over hot cake.
Combine oleo, 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1/2 cup Milnot until butter is melted.
Add the chocolate chips and almonds.
Pour over cake.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cool and remove from bone, discarding bone and skin.
Save broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces and place in a 9 x 13 baking pan.
In a saucepan, bring to boil the broth and chicken soup.
Pour it over the chicken.
In a bowl, combine the flour, salt, pepper, buttermilk, and melted margarine.
Mix well and pour the batter over the top of the chicken and broth.
Bake at 375° until brown on top.

title: pumpkin patch pie
directions: Place sherbet in bowl; stir until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Sprinkle with chopped Oreo cookies, pressing firmly into sherbet.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip. Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put contents in baking dish; stir and bake 1 hour.
If baking dish is not Teflon, grease pan with butter.

title: italian cheesecake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake according to directions on box and pour into pan.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat eggs into sugar, then add vanilla and Ricotta cheese and mix slightly.
Carefully pour this mixture over cake batter, not allowing mixture to touch the sides of the pan.
Bake
1 hour at 350° or until done.
Cool completely before adding cherry topping. Best served chilled.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Take one tablespoon of the mixture and roll into a ball.
Continue until all dough is rolled into balls.
Kids love making these!

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and bell pepper in skillet.
Layer Doritos in bottom of casserole.
Add soups and tomatoes to meat.
Pour over Doritos.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad waldorf
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add chicken, apples, celery and walnuts.
Mix well. Yields 5 or 6 cups.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, cracker crumbs, egg, onions, 1/3 cup tomato sauce, salt, oregano and pepper; mix well.
Shape into a flat rectangle, about 10 x 12-inches, on waxed paper.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over meat mixture.
Roll up jelly roll fashion. Press ends to seal.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain off excess fat.
Pour on remaining tomato sauce.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: beau monde dip in rye bread
directions: Scoop out center of loaf, leaving crust intact.
Tear removed portion into bite size pieces.
Combine next 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into cavity in loaf.
Garnish with fresh parsley sprigs.
Serve with reserved pieces of rye bread.
You may want to have another loaf available for dipping!

title: pineapple dressing(ham's best friend)
directions: Cream oleo; add sugar and beaten eggs.
Add pineapple and stir in cubed bread.
Bake in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 45 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Cut margarine into Bisquick and sugar.
Add the 1/2 cup of milk and stir just until mixed.
Drop by the spoonfuls on top of fruit and spread lightly to cover fruit.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons of cornstarch.
Sprinkle over top of dessert. Then pour 1 cup boiling water over all and bake at 375° to 400° until done.
Use 1 1/2-quart size lightly greased casserole.

title: sweet dill pickles(easy way)
directions: Pour off juice from cucumbers; add sugar and spices.
Seal in jar.
Turn upside down about 2 or 3 times.
Makes its own juice.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Saute onions in butter.
Mix all ingredients; add salt and pepper.
Place in casserole.
Stir in cheese and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Servings:

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Slowly add sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold in other ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop cookies by teaspoon onto ungreased foil-covered cookie sheet.
Put cookies in oven and turn off heat.
Leave cookies in closed oven overnight.

title: date and marshmallow loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in mold lined with wax paper. Chill.
Unmold when ready to use.

title: better than robert redford
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Mix and press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread this on crust.
Mix 2 packages instant pudding with 2 1/2 cups milk.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Spread on top of cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and chill.
Serves 12.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix sugar and Karo first.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat good after each.
Add salt, vanilla and melted oleo. Add pecans last.
Cook 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pound cake
directions: Prepare cake by directions + 1 egg. Add icing to mix; beat with mixer. Spray large Bundt pan with nonstick spray. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar (or granulated). Pour mix into pan. Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: kentucky hot brown(for 1 serving)
directions: Melt cheese in turkey gravy; set aside.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown beef with chopped onion.
Add tomato paste and chili powder and stir in well.
Add tomato sauce, consomme and water. Simmer all of this for 15 minutes.
Add cooked and drained spaghetti.
Put in casserole.
When ready to serve, heat in 350° oven until bubbly hot.
Serve with Parmesan cheese on top. Freezes well.

title: cranberry cream pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in powdered sugar.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Fold in thawed Cool Whip. Divide filling between the two pie crusts.
Freeze.

title: aunt clara's stone jar nut cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt, vanilla and nutmeg.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Sift flour with soda. Add half of the flour to mixture; add milk and remaining ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon on greased baking sheet and pat down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bachelor vegetable soup
directions: Cut up and cook potatoes in saucepan. In large pot, add cut up corned beef, chopped onions, corn, green beans, peas, tomato paste, kidney beans and stewed tomatoes. When potatoes are done, add those to soup. Cook on low for about 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until done.

title: pot roast medley
directions: You will also need 1 roasting plastic bag with seasoning mix.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush
cookies; set aside.
Make pudding as directed on box and add cream cheese, butter, powdered sugar and vanilla. Fold in Cool Whip.	Layer in a deep bowl or flower planter the cookies
on bottom,
worms
next and pudding.	Continue until mixture is gone.
You can add a fake flower for decoration.

title: pot liquor soup
directions: Remove stems and rinse collards.
Drain and tear into 1-inch pieces.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; drain.
Repeat.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown meat with green peppers in a large pot. Add onion soup mix, garlic powder, salt and chili powder. Mix well. Add remaining ingredients and cook until potatoes are done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix and bake in greased baking dish at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: french spaghetti
directions: Saute butter, onions, peppers and mushrooms together.
Add tomatoes and salt.
Simmer, uncovered, for 40 minutes.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Peel and wash shrimp.
Make roux by heating grease in deep skillet with flour.
Cook on medium heat until dark brown, stirring constantly.
Add onions, peppers, celery and garlic.
Add Ro-Tel and tomato sauce.
Season with salt and pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer covered 30 minutes.
Bring to boil; add shrimp.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: fitz's chip dip
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Fold in whipping cream.

title: aloha banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients except coconut and nuts.
Blend at low speed until dry ingredients are moistened.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes. Stir in coconut and nuts.
Turn into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan which has been greased on the bottom.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan immediately.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.
It's best made the day before.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: berta's delicious oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, egg, water and vanilla.
Combine remaining ingredients, using choice of two of the last three ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Measure flour; sift with soda, salt and spices.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add beaten egg, then add applesauce.
Add flour and stir in raisins.

title: fruit compote
directions: Combine tapioca and water and let stand 5 minutes.
Cook and stir over medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and blend in sugar, salt and juice concentrate.
Cool, stirring occasionally.
Cover and chill.
Before serving, fold in fruits: fresh fruits or frozen fruits work best.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Melt oleo and add brown sugar, cinnamon, vanilla, milk and pudding mix.
Bring to boil and then pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cut up bread dough into 1-inch pieces into the caramel mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for a few minutes, then turn onto cookie sheet.

title: pickled ham
directions: Place 4 to 6 thick (1/2 to 3/4-inch) pork chops in shallow oiled pan.
Spoon undiluted condensed canned cream of mushroom soup over top of each chop.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients and pat thin on a pizza pan (lightly sprayed with Pam).
Cook at 350° until light brown.
Let cool.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add crushed potato chips and pecans.
Add flour.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned (15 to 18 minutes).

title: brown country gravy
directions: In
a
frypan
pour in cooking oil.
Heat over a medium fire. Add flour
slowly, stirring constantly.
Let cook until the mixture is a
golden
brown.
Add
water gradually until a medium thick gravy is
made.
Add the salt, pepper, Accent and the beef base.
Cook over
a
low
fire
for
another
5 to 10 minutes. Makes enough to serve 8 to 12.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Line a pan with tortilla chips. Add a layer of chicken mixture.
Then a layer of chips.
Continue layering until all mixture is used.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pasta and beans (white)(one pound is never enough for the rodio's)
directions: Put chicken in a single layer in a roasting pan.
Combine other ingredients in a bowl and pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in the water.
Add the flour. Bring to a boil and let cool. Slowly beat in the eggs, one at
a time. Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: southwest rice
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, saute the green pepper, onion and garlic in oil for 3 minutes. Stir in the broth, rice, cumin and turmeric. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until rice is tender. Add beans, tomatoes and corn. Heat through. Yield: 8 servings.

title: low calorie hot dish(tastes like cabbage rolls without all the work)
directions: Chop cabbage in large pieces and place in the bottom of a greased baking dish.
Brown meat and onion; pour off fat and stir in rice.
Pour meat over cabbage and cover all with soup and water.
Bake in preheated oven for at least an hour at 350°. Watch to see that it doesn't get dry and add a little more water if necessary.
This recipe can be varied by using sausage, chops, etc. and whatever seasonings you prefer, but in that case, forget the weight watching.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and butter with mixer. Add flour, then mix. Add nuts then mix all together with spoon. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake 25 - 30 minutes at 350° (don't overcook).

title: kathy allen's lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade and milk.
Fold in topping until smooth.
Pour into pie crusts.
Refrigerate before serving.
May be frozen.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix together well. Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: cottage cheese kuchen
directions: Cream together all ingredients with mixer except cinnamon. Pour over crust and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together in a salad bowl.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and add to broccoli mix.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter, sugar and milk.
Bring to boil, boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and quickly add remaining ingredients; stir. Spoon onto wax paper and let cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese.
Add peanut butter and sugar.
Continue whipping while slowly adding milk.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into crust.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: swiss vegetable medley casserole(ready to bake in 5 minutes.)
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup shredded cheese, sour cream and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer, so cheese will melt. Serves 6.

title: rhubarb juice
directions: Cut rhubarb into 4-inch pieces; put in steamer.
While rhubarb is steaming, mix rest of ingredients in a kettle and heat.
Add rhubarb juice as taken off of steamer.
Bring to near boiling point.
Put into hot jars and seal.

title: della's taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger and onion on medium heat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain fat.
Add beans, soup, taco seasoning mix and 1 soup can of water.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Layer meat mixture with tortillas, cheese, meat, tortillas, cheese, etc., in a 2-quart casserole baking dish.
Top with grated cheeses and heat thoroughly until casserole bubbles.

title: molasses sugar cookies(makes dozens!)
directions: Melt butter over low heat and cool.
Add sugar, molasses and eggs and beat well.
Sift remaining ingredients together and add to molasses mixture, mixing well.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Dip tops into granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: old-fashioned thick eggnog
directions: In electric mixer, beat egg yolks with sugar until thick. Slowly add bourbon and cognac.
Chill 2 hours.
Meanwhile, add salt to egg whites and beat until almost stiff.
Whip cream until stiff.
Fold whipped cream into yolk mixture, then fold in beaten egg whites.
Chill 2 hours.
When ready to serve, sprinkle with nutmeg and serve in cups with a spoon.
If desired, add 1 or 2 cups of milk to the yolk mixture for a thinner eggnog.

title: country chicken casserole(great over hot cooked rice)
directions: In 3-quart casserole, cook garlic, onion and green pepper, covered, on High for 4 to 6 minutes, until tender, stirring halfway through cooking.
Stir in flour until blended, then tomatoes with their liquid, raisins, half of curry powder (1 1/2 teaspoons) and salt, stirring to break up tomatoes.
Add chicken pieces, arranging meatier portions toward edge of casserole.
Sprinkle chicken with remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons curry powder.
Cook, covered, on High 20 to 24 minutes, until chicken juices run clear, stirring mixture and rearranging chicken halfway through cooking.
Makes 4 servings.

title: democrat cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve at room temperature or chilled.

title: carrots tarragon
directions: Prepare carrots as per instructions on bag, or boil fresh carrots for 10 minutes, then cover and simmer for additional 5 minutes, or until tender-crisp.
While carrots are cooking, simmer 3 to 4 tablespoons butter in small saucepan.
When butter is melted, stir 2 tablespoons tarragon into butter.
Remove butter-tarragon mixture from stove top; stir in the brown sugar. Remove carrots from stove top when tender; drain.
Place carrots in serving bowl and pour tarragon-butter-brown sugar mixture over top. Mix together.
Cover and serve!

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream and pack 1/2 cup butter, 1/4 cup powdered sugar and 1 cup sifted flour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.
Top with 1/2 stick butter, crushed crackers and 1/2 cup almonds.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing, mustard and honey.
Place chicken on greased grill over medium-hot coals.
Brush with half of the sauce. Grill 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn; brush with remaining sauce.
Grill 8 to 10 minutes until tender.

title: sheet cake
directions: Melt oleo, cocoa and water together.
Mix sugar, flour and soda; mix well with first liquid mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla; mix until air bubbles are almost gone.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch dessert cookies
directions: Cream oleo, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Beat well until light and fluffy.
Add soda, baking powder and salt.
Alternate sour cream and flour; blend well.
Chill for several hours or overnight.

title: brownies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add shortening, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix at medium speed for 5 minutes, scraping sides of bowl often.
Pour into greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy "toffee" candy
directions: Heat oven to 425°. In medium saucepan melt 1/4

cup butter. Pour evenly into heavy duty foil lined 15x10-inch jellyroll pan. Arrange crackers over butter; cut crackers to fill empty spaces. Melt remaining butter in same saucepan; stir in sugar. Bring to a boil over medium heat; reduce heat and cook for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat; stir in sweetened condensed milk. Spread evenly over crackers.

title: chicken breasts with tomato butter
directions: Combine 3 tablespoons of butter with the garlic, tomato paste and parsley.
Scrape onto a piece of plastic wrap and use the wrap to help form a cylinder.
Wrap tightly and chill.
Combine flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Dredge chicken in the flour mixture.
In a large frying pan, melt remaining 1 tablespoon butter in the oil over medium high heat.
Add chicken and reduce heat to medium.
Cook turning once until chicken is just done, about 15 minutes.
Top hot chicken with slices of tomato butter.

title: blitz kuchen
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Beat in separately the eggs.
Stir in the flour.
Spread paper thin in large cookie sheet greased and floured.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over the top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cut in squares while hot.
Serve with coffee.

title: fresh apple muffins
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; mix well.
In a small bowl, combine egg, oil and milk.
Stir in apples.
Add egg mixture all at once to flour mixture.
Fill each cup 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Make potatoes as on box.
Mix cheese and dip in potatoes.
Put in casserole dish; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: baked zucchini squash
directions: Place cut zucchini in saucepan.
Add just enough water to cover.
Boil 5 minutes or until barely tender.
Drain and cool. Scoop out squash pulp and place in bowl, reserving squash hulls.

title: bohunk slop
directions: Fry potatoes until almost done.
Add rest of ingredients. Turn heat to medium-low; cook 10 more minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: baked beef ziti(lighter eating - 6 points)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook pasta according to pkg. directions without added fat or salt; drain and set aside. Meanwhile, heat oil in medium saucepan over medium heat; add garlic and saute 2 minutes. Add beef and cook until browned, breaking up meat as it cooks, about 3-5 minutes; drain off any fat and return pan to heat. Add oregano, thyme, rosemary, salt and pepper; stir to coat beef. Cook until herbs become fragrant, about 2 minutes. Add tomatoes and bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes. Spoon a small amount of tomato mixture into the bottom of a 4-qt. casserole dish (just enough to cover the surface). Top with half of ziti and then layer with half of the remaining sauce and half of the cheese. Layer remaining ziti on top and top with remaining sauce and cheese. Bake until cheese is golden and bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add egg and milk; mix.
Break up salmon and add to mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil and cook about 4 minutes.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place melted butter into a large bowl. Add cocoa and stir until well blended.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, vanilla extract and salt.
Stir until mixed together.
Stir in chocolate chunks and nuts.
Spread batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake for about 30 minutes or until done.
Cool and cut into serving size pieces.

title: cindy fowler's dump cake
directions: Layer apples with dry cake mix on top.
Cover with pats of margarine or butter.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: joggin in a jug
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: carrot salad
directions: Slice carrots and cook until almost done (tender).
Boil tomato soup, sugar, oil and vinegar for 5 minutes and add celery seed and mustard seed.
Pour over sliced carrots and chill.
Keeps for several days.

title: snicker salad
directions: Beat frozen Snicker bars with hammer into small pieces.
Cut apples into bite-size chunks.
Mix Snicker pieces, apple chunks and Cool Whip.
Serve.

title: cran-apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel, core, and slice apples, then combine with cranberry sauce and orange rind; set aside.
Mix together oats, flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, and salt; cut in margarine or butter until crumbly mixture forms.
Press a third of the mixture over bottom of greased 8 x 8 x 2 inch pan.
Spread with fruit, then top with remaining oat mixture.
Bake 45 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm with ice cream.
Makes 9 servings.

title: sicilian meat loaf
directions: Mix all except ham and shredded and sliced cheese with the ground meat.
On foil or wax paper, put meat mixture into a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Add ham slices on top of meat, leaving a small margin around edges.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over ham.
Starting at short end, carefully roll up meat, using foil or wax paper to lift.
Seal all edges.
Place roll, seam down, in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Place cheese slices over top of roll; return to oven for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: southwest tomatillo chicken
directions: Dice chicken; marinate in Garlic Herb Marinade for 35 to 45 minutes.
Dice all vegetables.
Saute, stir-fry chicken and marinade in skillet until cooked.
Add vegetables and stir.
Pour in precooked rice.
Stir.
Add 1/3 jar Tomatillo Chutney.
Stir in until mixed.
Garnish with almonds and squeeze lime juice over. Serve.

title: apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice and add to it flour mixed with sugar. Beat in egg and cider vinegar or cider.
Cook until thick.
Cool. Add to apple chunks, pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.

title: skillet supper
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing between each addition.
Heat until hot and serve.

title: sausage roll-ups
directions: Roll crescent rolls out flat.
Brush with mixture of softened butter, Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Place sausage links on rolls; wrap once.
Slice into 4 or 5 pieces; secure with toothpicks.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: spicy deer burger
directions: Make deer burger into small patties; dredge in flour and salt and pepper.
Brown in oil on both sides of burgers.
In a small bowl, mix ketchup, water or broth and Tabasco; pour over the meat in skillet.
Simmer over medium to low heat for 30 minutes, turning once.
(Sauce should be thick when done.)

title: chad's favorite cornbread
directions: Using your own favorite cornbread mixture, pour into a greased and floured iron skillet on which the bottom has been lined with bacon pieces or sliced middling meat.
Bake until well done.
The bacon will brown on bottom of cornbread.
Serve with cold, sweet milk, onions and pinto beans.
"Delicious."

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: double cheese macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to pkg. directions. Alternate layers of macaroni, cheddar and cottage cheese in greased 2 qt. baking dish, beginning with macaroni and ending with cheese. Melt the butter in saucepan. Stir in the flour to make a smooth mixture. Blend in milk gradually. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Cook until sauce has thickened- about 2 minutes. Add salt and pepper. Pour sauce over macaroni and cheese. Mix bread crumbs with 2 Tbsp. butter. Sprinkle over macaroni and cheese. Bake at 375° for 30-35 minutes.

title: sweet sour orange pork chops
directions: Brown chops in margarine.
Transfer to casserole and cover with sliced onions.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt oleo in bowl; add remaining ingredients.
Roll in little balls and put on wax paper.

title: pork and beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 3 hours at 350°, covered. Remove cover the last 1/2 hour (1 1/2 hours if recipe is cut in half).

title: wash pot stew
directions: Boil chickens and discard bone and skin.
Cook butter beans and blend in blender, all except 1-quart.

title: chicken livers and rice
directions: Saute butter, onions, oregano, rosemary and thyme.
Cut chicken livers into bite
size
pieces and add to mixture when onions are soft.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook rice and mix with the chicken liver mixture.
Add small amount of water or broth, if needed.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of oleo and pour over graham cracker crumbs. Toss and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
On high speed, beat for several minutes: eggs, 1 stick oleo and powdered sugar.
Pour over crust.
Slice bananas and arrange over cream mixture.
Drain pineapple until it's as dry as possible and sprinkle over banana. Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Decorate cherry halves.
Keep refrigerated.

title: redskin salmon salad
directions: Heat 1 inch depth of water to boiling.
Add potatoes.
After 15 minutes of cooking time, add broccoli.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add zucchini.
Cook until vegetables are tender, a total of 20 minutes cooking time.
Drain well.
Add olives, dill, salmon and dressing; toss to mix.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Add pepper and onion; toss to mix.
Serve chilled.
Serves 6.

title: white orange fruit cake
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
(Take 1/2 cup of this dry mixture and mix with pecans, cherries, raisins, candied orange peel and grated rind.)
Beat together butter and 1 cup sugar in large bowl until smooth.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with buttermilk until blended.
Gently stir in pecan mixture.
Spoon batter into small loaf tins.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes until a wooden pick comes out clean.
While these are baking, combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup orange juice in small saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
When cakes are done, remove from oven.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Prick holes in cakes with long tined fork or skewers and spoon orange syrup over cakes.
Wrap in foil and store.
Keep in cool place 4 weeks.
It is important that no substitutions be made for this recipe.

title: creme de menthe delight
directions: Prepare the cake mix according to directions, adding 3 tablespoons of green creme de menthe.
Cool the cake for at least 1 hour (9 x 13-inch pan).
Spread chocolate fudge over the cake.
To 12 ounce container of Cool Whip, add 3 tablespoons green creme de menthe and mix well.
Spread over the cake and chocolate topping; sprinkle nuts or chocolate jimmies over the top of cake.

title: salmon ball
directions: Blend until smooth onion, green onion, celery and bell pepper. Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheets.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: s'mores
directions: Add 1 marshmallow to 1 graham cracker and 1 chocolate square. Then put 1 graham cracker on top.
Place on wax paper and put in microwave for 30 seconds on High.
May add peanut butter if desired.

title: million-dollar fudge
directions: Heat sugar, butter, salt and evaporated milk over low heat, stirring until the sugar dissolves.
Bring to boil; boil for 6 minutes.
Put chocolates, marshmallow cream and nut meats in bowl. Pour the boiling syrup over the ingredients; beat until the chocolate is all melted.
Pour in a greased pan.
Cool for several hours before cutting into squares.
Store in a tin.

title: peanut setting pretties cookies
directions: Blend the oleo or butter and brown sugar.
Stir in the egg yolk and vanilla.
Mix in the flour and salt.
Chill for 1 hour. Roll in 1-inch balls.
Dip in slightly beaten egg white, then roll in nuts.
Bake for 5 minutes at 350°.
Press thumb in center of each; bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool.
Fill with frosting; garnish with M&M's peanuts.
Makes 2 dozen.
(Amount of vanilla frosting and M&M's makes triple batch.)

title: ham and pea salad
directions: In a serving bowl, combine the peas, ham, cheese and onion. Pour dressing over the top; toss to coat evenly.
Yields 6-8 servings.

title: sherried beef
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Serve on rice.

title: clarified butter
directions: Place butter in 2-cup glass measure.
Cook on 20% power for 3 1/2 minutes.
Let stand 3 to 4 minutes.
Skim foam from top. Slowly pour off yellow oil into small serving dish.
This is the clarified butter.
Discard the leftover impurities.
Serve as dipping sauce for clams, crab legs, lobster or shrimp.

title: apple-pie filling
directions: Boil until little thick.
Pour over apples in jar.
This will do 7 quarts.
Do not pack apples too tight so filling will go in jars.
Pressure cook 10 to 15 minutes at 5 pounds pressure.

title: dip
directions: With mixer, blend
first
two ingredients.
Stir in the rest. Serve with corn chips.

title: fudge marshmallow candy
directions: Microwave chocolate chips with peanut butter on Medium for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir after every minute.
Add marshmallows.
Chill until firm.

title: willis' sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: root beer
directions: Mix thoroughly and be sure when pouring into bottle not to fill to top.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; blend in egg. Stir together salt, baking powder, flour and vanilla and add to mixture. Mix all together and cool in refrigerator. Roll out on floured board and cut into shapes with cookie cutters. Bake at 325° for about 10 minutes or until done.

title: pot roast
directions: Put all ingredients in a pot and cover.
Cook 2 1/2 hours on medium to low light on the stove top.
Do not open pot before 2 1/2 hours.
Keep pot tightly covered.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni 8 to 10 minutes and drain. Combine all other ingredients.
Add macaroni.
Put in buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° about 35 to 45 minutes. Top with chopped fresh tomatoes or salsa.

title: mini-meatball surprise
directions: Mix hamburger with other ingredients, except for soup and milk.
After mixing items together well form small meatballs. Brown over medium heat; drain.
Remove from pan.
Heat soup and milk; add meatballs.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles and veggies.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cook zucchini and lemon juice together.
Add sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Simmer about 1 minute.

title: crusty pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Sift flour 3 times; measure 2 cups plus 2 tablespoons.
Cream shortening and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs alternately with flour, beating well after each addition.
Add salt and vanilla; beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Increase oven temperature to 325°.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Do not open oven door during baking time.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: easy homemade biscuits
directions: Sift flour.
Add melted shortening and sugar.
Add buttermilk; stir until dough can be dropped by large spoonfuls into flour to be coated.
Place biscuits on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: slumgolian
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Heat mushroom soup with 1/2 can water; set aside.
Layer bottom of casserole dish with tortillas; layer hamburger meat and cheese (several layers) until pan is near full, cheese being top layer.
Then put can of chili peppers, spreading across top.
Pour mushroom soup mixture over the top.
If desired, add another layer of cheese and green onions.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: jeannie fuger's fruit crust pizza
directions: Mix first six ingredients and bake on two pizza pans (line pans with waxed paper) 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cover cooled crusts with Cool Whip (1/2 large carton on each) and top with fruit (strawberries, pineapple, bananas, cherries, peaches and kiwi).
Put peaches and bananas in lemon juice first to keep from turning dark.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown meat in butter until well cooked.
Cook rice until done. Thoroughly rinse rice in cold water.
Cook onions and tomatoes for 20 minutes.
In a baking dish, layer tomato soup, pimiento, meat, tomatoes and onions and cooked rice; repeat.
Season with salt, pepper and sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat egg and add shortening, orange juice and hot water.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Add nuts and cranberries.
Bake in 9 x 5-inch greased and floured pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
Brush bread top with
butter.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Stir all ingredients, except shells, well.
Pour half into 1 shell, the other half into remaining shell.
Cool for 2 hours. Ready to serve.
Recipe makes 2 pies.

title: green pea salad
directions: Place lettuce in the bottom of dish.
Pour peas over lettuce. Add onion rings.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream.
Spread over the top.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: punch(non alcoholic)
directions: Mix to your own taste all ingredients.
You may leave the strawberries frozen and that will keep your punch cold longer. Sherbet should be put in scoops, not whole.

title: glazed fresh apple cookies(yields 3 dozen)
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat brown sugar and shortening with an electric mixer until well blended.
Beat in egg until fluffy.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Blend egg yolks, sugar, salt & nutmeg with whisk. Slowly pour in scalded milk. Add vanilla. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 450 degrees for 15 minutes. Bake another 25-30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: perfect rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Pour milk over shortening and sugar.
Add 1/2 of the flour and mix, then add remaining flour and yeast.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand for 15 to 20 minutes, then use as much of the dough as needed.
Store remaining dough in refrigerator.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: stoby's cheese dip
directions: Bring the water, Coffee-mate, mustard powder, garlic powder and cumin to a boil.
Add the Velveeta.
Mix butter (melted) and flour
and add to first mixture.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Temperature varies; does best on simmer.

title: hot catsup
directions: First of all, be careful of your selection. Once selected, give your entire thought to preparation for domestic use.

Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, others are constantly getting them in hot water. This makes them sour, hard and sometimes bitter. Even poor varieties may be made sweet and tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with love and seasoned with kisses. Keep warm with a steady fire of domestic adoration and serve with peaches and cream. Thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Cream together. Pour on top of congealed salad. Enjoy.

title: raisin bars
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup sugar.
Cut in 1/3 cup margarine until crumbly.
Press into bottom of lightly greased 9-inch square pan.
(I use Pam spray.)
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Saute vegetables in broth or margarine until soft, but not brown.
(To cut calories, cook vegetables in a little water.)
Add chicken and soup; mix and heat through.

title: easy quiche
directions: Mix together in large bowl, eggs, sour cream and grated Swiss cheese, then stir in all of your favorite quiche ingredients. Pour the mixture into pie shell.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top, forming 1/4-inch layer.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes to an hour.
Check to make sure it is firm in the center.
Let stand for 15 minutes before cutting.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil cabbage leaves about 5 minutes until tender.
Mix all other ingredients and form into 9 balls.
Wrap balls in cabbage leaves.
Place in baking dish.
If desired, pour tomato juice and/or sauerkraut over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: tennessee fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine. Add sugar and cocoa. Stir well and add eggs. Stir don't beat. Add milk and vanilla.

title: pork with cabbage
directions: Marinate sliced pork with soy sauce and sesame oil.
Add 2 tablespoons peanut oil to a preheated wok.
Stir-fry pork until meat changes color.
Pull pork up the sides of the wok.

title: butterscotch frosting
directions: Melt butter in pan and add brown sugar.
Cook until sugar is melted, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire and add milk and vanilla.
Mix.
Add confectioners sugar and mix thoroughly.
A little more sugar or milk may be added if necessary to gain the right consistency to spread on cake, or if a little more frosting is needed.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put down one layer of whole crackers. Mix pudding and milk. Add Cool Whip to mixture and mix well until thickened. Pour 1/2 of mixture over first layer of crackers. Add another layer of crackers. Pour remaining mixture on top. Add another layer of crackers and spread 1/2 of the icing over the top layer of crackers. Icing will need to be soft. Refrigerate for several hours to allow crackers to soften.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening, adding the powdered sugar and beating until smooth.
Then add the eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth after the addition of each egg.

Add the vanilla and flour, making sure that the mixture is completely smooth when finished. Bake in an angel food cake pan or small loaf pan (lightly greased) on the lowest rack of your oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool on a wire rack.
Cake can be frozen easily.

title: barbecue sauce 87'
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: ernie's christmas fruit salad
directions: Mix the orange juice and lemon juice together to form a citrus juice. As you chunk the apples, bananas, and pears, mix them into the prepared citrus juice. This will keep the fruit from turning dark. Mix in all other ingredients. Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cut ends off of zucchini and chop in blender until smooth.

title: pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle broken pecans on bottom of an unbaked pie shell. Melt butter.
Mix eggs, butter, sugars, syrup, vanilla and salt together.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until almost set.

title: terrific tex-mex salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except corn chips, tossing well to cover with dressing.
Transfer to large serving tray.
Surround with corn chips.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in one bowl until they are smooth; put in baking pan (8 x 10-inch).
Set oven at 425° and bake until light gold crust.

title: candied yams
directions: In a pan place yams and salt; cook and peel.
In a saucepan combine butter, brown sugar, orange peel, orange juice, cinnamon and pepper.
Slice yams and add to pan.
Heat to boiling.
Heat until yams are glazed, turning as needed to glaze both sides.
Add walnuts, if desired.

title: quick and tasty string beans
directions: Cook beans with seasoned salt.	While they are cooking, saute onion
and mushrooms in butter.
Drain string beans and toss
with onion and mushroom mixture.
Add Salad Supreme and chives.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in glass pie plate or Corning dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until top is golden brown.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Work in flour, vanilla and nuts. Shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
When cool, roll in confectioners powdered sugar.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla well.
Add flour, pecans and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes (13 x 9-inch pan). While hot, spread marshmallow cream on top.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar and stir over low heat about 2 minutes.
Do not let sugar melt.
Add butter and evaporated milk and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 1 minute; remove from heat and stir in vanilla.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Mix all together and put in a rather large pan.
(I use my little cooker.)
Bring to a good rolling boil. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 1/2 cups pecans. Beat with a spoon until it gets thick and creamy. Drop on wax paper by spoonfuls.
(If mixture gets too thick or hard, reheat just a little.)

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans together.
Shape into ball. Roll in pecans, refrigerate overnight.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix milk, potatoes, shortening, sugar and salt in large bowl; cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast softened in water.
Add eggs; add 1 1/2 cups of flour and beat well.
Add more flour; beat.
Add more flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out on a board and knead thoroughly.
Place dough in a greased bowl; grease top of dough; cover and let rise for 2 hours.
Turn out on floured board and roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into 2-inch diamond shapes.
Pull on opposite ends to elongate.
Dip in melted butter and lay alternately in buttered ring mold.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: one bowl chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, salt and cocoa into large mixing bowl.
Add shortening and 2/3 cup buttermilk.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed. Add remaining buttermilk and eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes. Use two greased 8-inch round layer pans or 13 x 9-inch cake pan (metal preferred).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: toasted coconut bread
directions: Mix milk, egg, oil and vanilla together.
Add dry ingredients; stir.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour until tester comes out clean.
Great sliced and toasted.

title: rosy poached pears
directions: Strain pear syrup into medium saucepan.
Add cranberry-apple juice.
Bring to a boil.
Add pear halves.
Simmer on low heat for 15 minutes.
Remove pears from liquid.
Reduce liquid until slightly thickened.
Pour over pears.
Refrigerate until cold. Serve in individual dessert dishes.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until thickened. Cool 1 hour.
Combine apples, pineapple, 1/2 cup nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix together with cooked, cooled sauce.
Sprinkle top with remaining nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and set aside.
Then mix remaining ingredients.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Put 1/4 of cake mixture on bottom of each pan, then add 1/4 cinnamon mixture, 1/4 cake mixture and top with rest of cinnamon mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: anna's orange jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix, Jell-O, eggs, Crisco and water well and pour into a greased and floured tube or loaf pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
While cake is baking, mix together sugar, juice and hot water.
As soon as cake is removed from oven, punch full of holes with a large fork.
Then spoon the juice mixture all over top of cake and let stand until completely cool.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage and cheese together.
Mix Bisquick until you can form one big ball.
Add a little more Bisquick if ball is real sticky.
Make into walnut-size balls and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: famous creole seasoning
directions: Two or 3 hog heads, skinned and cut in quarters by local butcher. Wash heads well to remove bone chips from cutting.
Cook heads in salt water until meat is tender and falling off bone. Remove from water and let cool just enough so you can handle it. Don't let it get cold.
If you do, it will be hard to season and mix.
Remove all the lean meat from the bones adding just enough of the fat to allow mixture to mold well (about 7 parts lean to 1 part fat).

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add Sourdough Starter and stir only until moistened.
Turn onto floured surface and knead until smooth.
Roll or pat 1/2 inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush with butter and let rise in warm place about 1 hour. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Set onion in middle and bake in oven at 250° to 300° for about 3 hours.
Serves 8.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Get a very large bowl.
Must be hand mixed, fun!
Cream together peanut butter and margarine (you can use a spoon for this).
Add sugar and stir well.
Add eggs, soda and oats (now use hands).
Add M&M's.
Make cookies whatever size you want on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, eggs, butter and vanilla well.
Stir in chocolate morsels, pecans and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until firm.

title: polish noodles and cabbage
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add onion and saute until soft. Add cabbage and saute 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Stir in caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Meanwhile, cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain well.
Stir noodles into cabbage mixture.

title: double boiler frosting
directions: Combine ingredients in top of double boiler with water boiling.
Beat or stir for 1 minute.
Use mixer and whip until mixture will hold a peak (about 4 minutes).
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Continue beating for about 1
1/2 minutes longer.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Trim crusts from bread slices, if desired. Lightly butter bread on both sides and cut into cubes. Brown chopped ham, bacon or sausage and place on bottom of lightly greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Place the cubed bread on top of the meat. Put the shredded cheese on top of the bread. Beat the eggs until foamy. Add the pepper, dry mustard and milk. Stir well and pour over the meat, bread and cheese. Add some extra shredded cheese on top. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Cook at 350° for 30 to 60 minutes.

title: paul newman cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch metal pan.
When done, remove cake from oven and poke holes in top of cake.
Pour condensed milk over cake and allow to cool.
Spread topping over cake when cooled.
Top with Cool Whip. Break up Heath bars and sprinkle on top.
Then refrigerate.

title: mom's broccoli quiche
directions: Prick bottom and sides of pie crust with fork.

Bake in a 450° oven for 5 minutes. Take out of oven and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese. Spread half the broccoli over Parmesan cheese and continue with half the Swiss cheese and half the green onions.
Repeat with remaining broccoli, Swiss cheese and green onions.
In a bowl, beat the eggs. Add chicken broth, cream and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over broccoli. Sprinkle top with remaining Parmesan cheese. Bake for 10 minutes at 450°, then 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Check quiche by using butter knife in center.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Mix pie filling and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add cola, pecans and pineapple.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Beat whipped topping and cream cheese in a bowl until smooth.
Spread over gelatin.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: zucchini torte
directions: Beat eggs; add cheese, oil and chopped onion.
Fold in Bisquick.
Add diced zucchini, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 435 minutes.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Combine
soup,
rice,	butter	and
water.
Pour
over chicken breasts
in casserole.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350° and uncover and bake for 1/2 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and keep refrigerated.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and place into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Press firmly. Add seasoned bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until bubbly.

title: christmas dream fudge
directions: Mix sugar, salt and milk and bring to boil, then cook over medium heat 4 1/2 minutes, exactly, stirring constantly, to prevent scorching.
Break chocolate bar; mix with chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and butter.
Pour hot mixture over chocolate mixture and mix thoroughly.
Let stand a few minutes, then beat until very creamy.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into large, flat pan (cookie sheet with sides).
Cut into squares when cool. Makes 6 pounds.

title: mom's old-fashioned applesauce bread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Beat egg into applesauce. Add to dry ingredients with melted shortening.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake bread in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cold buttermilk soup
directions: Beat egg and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add buttermilk and lemon rind.
Serve cold topped with whipped cream, crushed corn flakes or toasted rolled oats.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Mound in dish.
Serve with Bremner wafers.

title: turkey breast
directions: After turkey breast has been washed and cleaned, place in roast pan.
Baste with margarine.
Sprinkle with dry ingredients. Paprika is the last to be sprinkled on for browning.
Bake in a covered roast pan at 350° for 30 minutes to the pound.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk and margarine and boil for 1 hour in a double boiler, stirring occasionally. Mix together the eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla and stir into the hot mixture. Pour into an oven-safe dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes with the pan set in hot water. Stir once after 15 minutes and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Raisins can be added.

title: pecan balls
directions: Mix sugar and oleo; gradually add sifted flour.
Stir in pecans, vanilla and nutmeg.
Shape into size of pecan in palm of hand.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 325° for 20 minutes or until done, not brown.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.
I cook these slower than 325°.
Use lots of powdered sugar to roll them in.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Simmer all ingredients together 1 1/2 hours.
Serve hot.

title: golden sunbeam cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together 3 times; set aside.
Beat egg yolks until very thick and fluffy.
Gradually beat in the sugar.
Add the next 3 ingredients, then fold in flour.
Mix gradually.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan, ungreased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Invert pan to cool.

title: raisin-yogurt muffins
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease 12 muffin cups or use paper liners. In one mixing bowl, cream together until light and fluffy softened margarine, sugar and salt.
In the other bowl, beat eggs and blend in plain yogurt, baking soda and flour.
Add this to the sugar and margarine mixture and stir only to blend.
The batter will be slightly lumpy.
Add the raisins during the last few strokes.
Fill each muffin cup two-thirds full.
Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes.

title: 100 cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar, margarine, oil, egg, vanilla, Rice Krispies, oats, raisins (if desired), nuts and/or coconut, if desired.
Sift together remaining ingredients; add sugar to mixture and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Let cool on sheet before removing.

title: sweet potato hot rolls
directions: Grease two 8 to 9-inch round cake pans.
In large bowl, combine flour mixture with yeast from foil packet, wheat germ and sugar; mix well.
Stir in hot water, sweet potatoes, margarine and 1 egg until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Put dough on lightly floured surface, grease and flour hands; shape dough into ball. Knead for 5 minutes until smooth; sprinkle with flour if dough becomes sticky.
Cover dough with large bowl; let rest 5 minutes. Divide dough into 16 equal parts; shape into balls.
Pull edges under so top will be smooth.
Place 8 balls on each greased pan smooth side up.
Cover with towel and place in warm place to let rise until dough is light and double in size, about 30 minutes. Preheat oven to 375°; uncover dough.
In small bowl, beat eggs and water; brush over rolls, then sprinkle with wheat germ.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: rice pudding
directions: Do not use instant rice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish (sprayed with Pam).
Bake at 350° until set.

title: skyline dip
directions: Layer all ingredients in large casserole dish and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Place peaches in the pie shell.
Beat together remaining ingredients and spread over peaches.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 325° for 1 hour.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Combine flour, soda, salt and cocoa powder.
Add sugars and butter; beat well.	Add eggs and vanilla; beat
at
medium
speed until light and fluffy.
Add chocolate chips; blend at low speed just until combined.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake for 21 to 23 minutes.	Yields 4 dozen.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Pour into mixing bowl.
Beat in ice cream, one spoonful at a time.
Beat in cream cheese.
Stir in pineapple.
Pour into mold and refrigerate 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with nuts, cherries or berries.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and cut up chicken.
Mix both soups, salt and pepper plus 1 cup of broth.
To this, add chicken.
Mix well and pour in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Take remaining cup of broth and margarine; add stuffing mix.
Mix well.
Put over top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat baking sheet with Pam.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Place egg whites in shallow dish. Using fork, beat until mixed.
Pour bread crumbs onto wax paper. Dip each chicken piece in egg whites, then roll in bread crumbs. Place chicken pieces 1-inch apart on prepared baking sheet.
Then spray pieces with Pam.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until tender and browned.

title: holly wreath clusters
directions: Heat butter in a saucepan.
When it begins to melt, add marshmallows.
Stir until marshmallows melt.
Add food coloring. Stir to blend; add cornflakes.
Stir until coated.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Mix the mayo, soup, eggs and cheese together in blender; salt to taste.
Fold in broccoli; pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Place casserole dish in a shallow pan of water in oven and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
May be mixed a day in advance and kept in refrigerator.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix sugar and Karo syrup in large 3-quart pot.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
When a rolling boil is achieved, remove from burner and stir in peanut butter and Corn Flakes.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: dirt
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Beat pudding and milk until thickens; add Cool Whip and vanilla pudding.
Fold the two mixtures together.
Crush the Oreo cookies in a blender. Line a flower pot (coffee can) with aluminum foil.
Starting with the Oreo cookie crumbs, layer crumbs, pudding and crumbs until the container is full, ending with Oreo crumbs.
Wrap Saran or plastic around stem of artificial flowers and insert in the pot.
Serves 20 people.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in baking dish; spread Veg-All over chicken. Combine soups and stock, spread over Veg-All.
Combine margarine, flour and milk.
Pour over soup.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes or until crust is golden.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes.

title: melting moments(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Cream together the butter or margarine with sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in the egg and a few drops of vanilla.
Add the flour and mix to a stiff dough.
Make small balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: diet ambrosia
directions: Mix together and keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: hot cabbage slaw
directions: Melt margarine.
Chop cabbage and add to margarine along with salt and sugar.
Cook over medium heat until cabbage is done (don't overcook).
Take off heat; add vinegar first, then the cream. Sprinkle with black pepper and serve.
It's delicious.

title: iced tea nectar
directions: Dissolve tea in a large pitcher.
Stir in sugar until dissolved, then add pineapple juice, apricot nectar and orange and lemon juices.
Pour over ice in tall glasses.

title: oatmeal pies double for 2
directions: Mix altogether with a spoon.
Take fork and pierce the bottom of both pie crusts.
Preheat oven to 225 degrees.
Place crusts in oven.
Don't let them brown at all.
Just until air is out.
Then pour mixture in pie crusts.
Cover the edges of pie crust with tin foil.
Cook for 30 minutes, or until done.
Don't over cook.
You can also add 1/2 c. pecans or 1/2 c. coconut.

title: orange rolls
directions: Bring to a rolling boil; set aside to cool.

title: baked stuffed maine lobster tails
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Stuffing should be moist but not wet.
If it is too wet, add more crackers.
If it is too dry add another egg or more ketchup according to taste.

title: tomato - garlic zucchini bake
directions: Slices of zucchini and onion are quickly sauteed, then combined with tomato wedges, Swiss cheese, and sourdough bread crumbs in this Italian style side dish.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together real well.
Grease 8 x 11-inch pan.
Press firmly into pan.
Pour another 8 ounce can tomato sauce over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet and tangy chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken.
Place over low heat and cook until jelly has melted and sauce has blended smoothly. Arrange chicken in a baking pan, skin side up.
Pour sauce over chicken evenly.
Cover pan with foil and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Uncover pan and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Baste with pan juices twice during the last 30 minutes of baking.
Serve hot with pan sauce spooned over each serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: 1. Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Drain well. 2. Combine ingredients and add broccoli.
Pour into well greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish and top with cracker crumbs. 3. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread with pineapple
directions: Cream first four ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until done (1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes).

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, cut the powdered sugar into the peanut butter until the mixture is well combined. Crumble half of the mixture into the bottom of the pastry shell.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in pan.
Cook until thick. Pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip or your favorite meringue.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holy cake
directions: Season to taste with spices.
Last step, beat.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange blossom prune cake
directions: Place pitted prunes in saucepan; add water about 1 inch above the prunes.
Bring to boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Drain prunes, reserving 3/4 cup liquid.
Dice prunes.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Combine reserved liquid, eggs, oil and orange peel; add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in prunes and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes or until tests done.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: twice baked potato
directions: Scrub potatoes and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender (fork done).
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop insides into large bowl.
Be careful not to destroy shells.
Mix sour cream and Ranch dressing; add to potatoes with margarine. Mix with a fork until only small lumps are left.
Spoon mixture back into potato shells.
Place in foil-lined 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Top with grated cheese and bake 5 more minutes.
Top with bacon bits (if desired).

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, butter and walnuts.
Press in bottom of lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cooled crust.

title: mulligatawny soup
directions: In a 4 quart heavy bottom pot, melt butter on medium heat.
Add onions and cook till translucent.
Add carrots and cook for 2 minutes, add garlic and cook 1 minute.
Add potatoes and cook 2 minutes; add curry and almonds cook till smoky.
Add broth and cook till carrots and potatoes are tender.
Add heavy cream or coconut milk bring back to boil.
Just before serving add spinach, cilantro and season to taste.

title: dieter's oven-baked french fries
directions: Cut baking potatoes lengthwise into thin wedges, having washed them good.
Leave skins on.
Put Parmesan cheese and paprika into a plastic bag.
Shake to mix, then add the potato strips.
Shake to coat potatoes with mixture.
Remove from bag and place on cookie sheet and bake in 425° oven for 30 minutes or until crisp. Optional:
Spray cookie sheet with Pam before putting potatoes on it.
Serve with ketchup or salsa.
(Make your own vegetable oil spray using a flavorful oil and a spray bottle.)

title: fruit candies
directions: Grind the first 4 ingredients together.
Mix all ingredients in a big bowl; shape into balls.
Roll in coconut or dip in chocolate (melted chips plus 2 tablespoons of water).
Set on waxed paper.

title: special occasion cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash cherries and leave in juice. Combine all ingredients and stir until blended.
Pour into a small square baking pan (spray with Pam).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Drizzle sugar-free maple syrup over top.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes 64 squares.

title: sausage-mushroom breakfast casserole
directions: Spread croutons in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.

title: ice cream(portuguese)
directions: Mix the condensed milk with
the regular milk and the yolks. You take it before it starts to boiling.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients in the order listed. Bake in well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Makes about 4 dozen small squares.

title: shake and bake for chicken
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Dip chicken in milk, then shake and bake.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, over medium heat, cook and stir steak, mushrooms, onions in oleo until steak is browned and vegetables are tender.
Reduce heat, add flour. Cook and stir 1 minute.
Add water and boullion.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through. DO NOT BOIL.
Serve with hot noodles.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Chill mixing bowl, beaters and cream.
Melt marshmallows in milk over low heat.
Blend in dry lime Jell-O.
Place in fridge.

title: chili(power level:  high, 100%.  cooking time:  29 to 35 minutes)
directions: Place ground beef, onions, green pepper and garlic in a 3-quart casserole.
Microwave on High (100%) for 4 to 5 minutes until beef is no longer pink and vegetables are tender.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Microwave on High (100%) for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Stir after cooking.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Sift together cake mix and pudding mix.
Make well in center and add all other ingredients except chips.
Beat well; stir in chips with spatula.
Pour batter into tube pan and bake 55 minutes at 325°.
Cool on wire rack 5 minutes.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in baking dish.
Bake in the microwave 12 minutes on High or until done, turning dish occasionally.
Can also be cooked in conventional oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Beat vanilla and eggs by hand for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add to creamed mixture, then add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips or nuts and coconut.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool on wire racks.
Enjoy!

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Put in bowl the cottage cheese.
Sprinkle in dry Jell-O. Stir.
Add drained crushed pineapple; stir.
Add Cool Whip; chill.

title: frappe(bow ties)
directions: Cut butter with egg and egg yolks into small pieces.
Add sugar, salt, whiskey and vanilla.
Slowly add flour.
Chill dough for 1 hour or more.
Roll dough out on lightly floured surface to paper thinness.
Cut into 2-inch x 3-inch long strips.
Make slit in center and pull one end of the dough through to form a loose knot.
Fry in deep oil until light golden color.
Drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: asparagus-pea casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Layer peas, asparagus, mushrooms, sauce and crackers, using 1/2 of each.
Then repeat procedure with the remaining portions.
Cover and cook 20 minutes at 350°.
Then uncover and cook 10 more minutes (should be bubbling).

title: overnight fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding mix as directed on package, substituting the 1 1/2 cups pineapple liquid for milk.
Cool. When mixture is cool, fold in fruit and put in glass serving bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Apples are optional and, if used, add shortly before serving.
Serves 12 or more.
Nice for covered dish dinners.

title: favorite pot roast
directions: Brown roast on all sides in hot oil in a large Dutch oven; drain off drippings.
Place sliced onion on top of roast.
Combine consomme and next 5 ingredients; mix well and pour over roast. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables. Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender, adding extra water if needed.
Remove bay leaf and discard.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot rolls
directions: Add sugar, salt and shortening to scalded milk; let cool. Dissolve yeast in water.
Add eggs to yeast and shortening mixtures and add flour just enough to make a soft dough.
Let dough rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again. Shape into rolls.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cream
directions: Stir together the chocolate drink mix, powdered sugar, vanilla and whipping cream.
Chill 1 hour.
Whip until stiff.
Spread between layers on cake and on top.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage; drain all that grease.

title: mexican beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Add all other ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oven chicken
directions: Boil two black ducks in large pot of water with 2 large cut onions until tender.
(When leg pulls away from body, it is done.) Take out of pot and cool completely on wire rack.
Butter the breast and place 2 slices of bacon across each duck.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.
Take onions out of broth and cook dumpling in them (rolled).

title: sunshine yams
directions: Scrub yams.
Drop into boiling water.
Cover and cook until tender.
Drain, cool and peel.
(May also be peeled, sliced or diced and cooked in boiling water and drained.)
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Stir in apple juice and lemon juice.
Heat until mixture is bubbly and slightly thickened.
Add butter and lemon rind.
Mash or process yams with juice mixture. Place in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Dab with a little extra butter. Sprinkle with paprika.
