Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: death by cream cheese
directions: Line large Pyrex baking dish bottom with one package of rolls. Mix cream cheese, egg yolks, vanilla and sugar with electric mixer. Spread over dough.
Cover with remaining package of dough.
Beat egg whites with fork.
Spread over dough.
Sprinkle top with 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Nuts may be added.
Bake in 325° oven 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy cherry crunch
directions: Melt margarine and mix with cake mix.
Add chopped pecans and mix until crumbly.
Spread cherry pie filling in bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Crumble cake mixture over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until browned.
Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: special potatoes
directions: For best results, smash hash browns on cabinet several times before opening.
In a very large bowl, mix all ingredients together, except butter.
Melt butter completely; mix thoroughly into other ingredients.
Spread evenly into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Cook at 375° until top is brown, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and
salt.	Cut
in shortening with pastry blender until mixture is consistency of coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk; stir with
fork just
until
dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out onto
lightly floured board.
Knead gently, just until smooth. Roll
out	to 1/2-inch
thickness.
Cut
with
floured 2-inch cutter; place on baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 to 14 biscuits.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients into dough that is soft and pliable.
Run through #1 disc of cookie press into long strips on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch pieces while still warm, but let cool in pan.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Store in airtight plastic bag or cookie tin.
Makes 6 dozen.
Don't let them get brown or they'll be too done!

title: bean dip
directions: Mush avocado and lemon juice up well.
Place bean dip on bottom of bowl, then sour cream and taco mix.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add oil, coffee and milk.
Mix for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 2 minutes more.
Bake in two 9-inch greased and floured cake pans for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: vegetable dip or potato topper
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate. Serve as a dip for raw vegetables or on baked potatoes. Makes 3 cups.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients over medium heat until it thickens and makes a soft ball in cold water.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until stiff.
Pour on greased platter. Cool and cut in squares.

title: cheese roll or ball
directions: Cream all ingredients except nuts.
Add nuts and roll into ball or roll.
Roll in chili powder.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: tomato surprise
directions: Pour tomatoes into saucepan, saving can for mold.
Bring tomatoes to a boil; add jello and salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Add lemon juice or vinegar.
Pour into can.
Chill until firm.
Yields 2 cups, 4 size servings or 6 relish servings.

title: karo peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water.
Boil until forms soft balls in cool water.
Add peanuts, cook until turns amber color.
Remove from heat and add baking soda; stir well.
Pour into buttered pans.
May use pecans instead of peanuts for a great pecan brittle!

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix the flour, baking powder and sugar in a bowl.
Add the milk and butter and stir until mixed.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole and spread peaches over top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream.

title: skandinavians
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Heat buttermilk to boil.
Add 4 tablespoons of butter, the sugar and the salt.
Stir to melt butter; cool to lukewarm.
Add flour to make a soft dough.
Knead on floured board, adding more flour, if needed to prevent sticking.
Invert bowl over dough and let stand 15 minutes.
Punch down dough; roll out to a 12 x 20-inch rectangle.
Melt the remaining two tablespoons of butter and brush it over the surface. Sprinkle over half of the dough 1/3 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup walnuts.
Fold the other half over and press edges together.
Cut in about 22 strips, 3/4-inch wide.
Twist each strip and make into a ring.
Put on a greased baking sheet and let rise about 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and perk in electric percolator.
Makes 32 (4 ounce) servings.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Blend eggs with parmesan cheese. Mix with spaghetti. Then layer 1/2 of the spaghetti in 8 x 8 inch pan. Cover with spaghetti sauce, 1/2 cup shredded mozzarella. Then add another layer of spaghetti, sauce and cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 30 minutes. Removing foil for the last few minutes of baking.

title: filling for graham crackers
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to slow boil and boil 3 minutes. Pour over and mix the rest of ingredients.

title: denver chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and soda in bowl.
Bring butter, water and chocolate to a boil in saucepan.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it tests done.

title: corn pudding
directions: In mixing bowl, combine corn, well beaten eggs, sugar, salt and pepper.
To this, add 1/2 of butter or oleo (melted) and sprinkle flour into mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish and dot with rest of butter or oleo.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate bottom cupcakes
directions: 8 oz. cream cheese

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix with mixer.
Beat until very smooth.
Add just a drop of red food coloring to make it pale pink.
Delicious with strawberries, cantaloupe and honeydew.

title: favorite doughnuts
directions: Heat fat or oil (3 to 4 inches) to 375° in deep fat fryer or kettle.
Measure 1 1/2 cups flour and the remaining ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in remaining flour.
turn dough onto well floured cloth covered board.
Roll around lightly to coat with flour.
Roll dough gently 3/8-inch thick.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Makes 2 dozen doughnuts.

title: cream of corn soup
directions: Heat corn, onion and
cups
milk
to
scalding.
Melt butter. Blend in flour and
add
remaining milk gradually, stirring constantly. Heat to boiling and cook for
3 minutes.
Put corn in blender; blend at low speed.
Add to white sauce and season.
Very good!
Serves 8.

title: preppy mexican crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In skillet, brown ground beef, chili powder, salt and garlic until crumbly and light brown.
Drain; remove garlic.
In small bowl, combine olives, onion, sour cream and mayonnaise.

title: hutchins farm potato-zucchini casserole
directions: Wash and slice potatoes and layer in buttered casserole dish. Cover potato slices with chopped onion.
Make a white sauce by melting 3 tablespoons butter in saucepan over low heat.
Slowly stir in flour.
Add milk, stirring or whisking constantly.
Add salt, pepper and garlic.
Continue stirring over low heat until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Pour white sauce over top of potatoes and onions.
Arrange zucchini over grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 75 minutes or until potatoes and zucchini are tender and the sides are bubbly.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: mother's tea cakes
directions: Sift flour in a tray.
Make a hole in flour as for making biscuits.
Put all ingredients in the hole; work with fingers until well mixed and moderately stiff.
Roll thin, cut with cookie cutter and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in a hot oven.

title: double-decker confetti brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 13x9x2 inch baking pan; set aside.

title: salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cook over hot water (not boiling), stirring constantly until real thick.
Put in refrigerator and cool.
Whip the whipping cream until stiff. Thoroughly drain pineapple tidbits, mandarin oranges and white cherries.
Add fruit, marshmallows and nuts to yolk mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts in a large bowl.
Beat egg with a fork and stir in applesauce.
Add to bowl and stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and serve with cream cheese.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Combine vinegar, salt, pepper, Worcestershire and onion. Gradually whisk olive oil in, then mayonnaise and cheese.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add oil and powdered sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Flatten thin with fork.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.

title: barbecue beans and burger hot dish
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add to hamburger, bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 10 people.
Also freezes well.

title: grilled chicken salad
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry with paper towels.
Place in a plastic bag set in a shallow dish.
For marinade, stir together the 1/4 cup orange juice concentrate, the lemon peel, lemon juice, oil and garlic.
Pour over chicken.
Close bag.
Marinate in the refrigerator for 6 to 24 hours; turn bag occasionally.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Brown ground beef and onion; drain and place in greased pie dish. Mix milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper. Pour over beef and onion mixture. Bake for 25 minutes. Remove and top with tomatoes and cheese. Return to oven and bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean (5-8 minutes).

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mash together and put in greased casserole.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice.
When cool, add celery or apple, pineapple, cranberries and nuts.
Mix. Put in mold and refrigerate.

title: harvest cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and 1 tsp. vanilla.
(Walnuts can be added-optional.)

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in large bowl on High 2 to 3 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted.
Stir halfway through heating time.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sausage, spinach balls
directions: Mix all together.
Put in the refrigerator for one hour.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend softened cream cheese with Accent, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Chop onions and dried beef in food processor and add to cheese.
Place in mold and chill.
Remove from mold and cover in chives or dried beef.

title: hot sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
If desired to make hotter, add more horseradish.

title: raisin applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook raisins in water, until absorbed all water.
Add applesauce, eggs and oil, then remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in an 8-inch square pan (sprayed with Pam).
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: gelatin-wiches
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread gelatin mixture about 1/2-inch thick or 14 of the crackers; top with remaining crackers, pressing lightly and smoothing around edges with spatula.
Freeze until firm, about 3 hours.
Makes 14 sandwiches.

title: chili sauce
directions: Saute
the
onions, brown the hamburger.
Add all other ingredients and
simmer for 30 minutes.
I use the packages of chili
seasoning
(Durkee
or
McCormick).	This recipe serves about 85 for hot dogs or hamburgers for bible school.

title: rainbow ice cream dessert
directions: Tear cake into small pieces; divide into thirds and place in bowls. Sprinkle strawberry Jell-O (dry) over 1, lime over another and orange over another. Toss until coated. In a 10-inch tube pan, put strawberry pieces in bottom. Spoon strawberries over cake; spread 1/3 ice cream over strawberries. Repeat with lime, cherries, ice cream, orange cake, oranges and ice cream. Freeze until firm. Unmold on chilled plate. Cut about 10 minutes before serving.

title: jiffy gel sundaes
directions: Empty gelatin into medium bowl. Add boiling water.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Divide ice cream among 8 dessert dishes. Spoon hot gelatin over ice cream. The gelatin will thicken as it touches the ice cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: breakfast shake
directions: Sweeten to taste. Blend.

title: fairy drop cookies
directions: In medium bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt. In large mixing bowl, beat butter; add powdered sugar and 1 cup sugar. Beat until fluffy. Add oil, eggs and almond extract. Beat until combined. Gradually add dry ingredients, beating on medium speed until combined.
May have to mix by hand if too stiff. Cover and chill 30 minutes. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated.
Using a buttered spatula or wax paper, press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cut into 2-inch squares when cool.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the sugar, cinnamon and walnuts and/or chocolate chips.
Put half of the batter in a greased angel food cake pan or tube pan.

title: short-cut enchiladas
directions: Thicken chili sauce to gravy consistency.
Spread sauce over bottom of square baking pan.
Add layer of corn chips to amply cover bottom of pan.
Drizzle sauce over chips to cover; sprinkle 1/2 cheese mixture.
Repeat chips, chili and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Can use rest of chili sauce to add at the table, if desired.

title: quick mix spritz
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together.
With a pastry blender or 2 knives, cut the butter into the dry ingredients until the mixture is full of very fine lumps.
It will resemble pie crust or biscuit mix, although not as coarse.

title: red raspberry salad
directions: Drain raspberries and pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine fruit juices and orange juice (should be about 2 1/2 cups liquid). Combine boiling water and 1 cup fruit juice; bring to boil.
Add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Add remaining fruit juice. Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Blend all together.
Chill and serve on your favorite salad.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in water; stir in sweetened condensed milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla. Cool slightly.
Arrange two bananas on bottom of prepared pastry shell.
Pour filling over bananas; cover.
Chill for 4 hours or until set.
Spread top with whipped cream.
Also good as coconut cream pie.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift flour.
Cut in shortening.
Add sugar and sweet potatoes. Stir in milk.
Use a little more flour, if necessary, to make stiff dough.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into biscuits.
Bake at 450° until lightly browned. Butter while hot and serve.

title: chicken wings(makes 24)
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and pour on wings and set overnight. Pour in a pan and bake 50 to 60 minutes; uncover the last 20 minutes.

title: pecan-coconut pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix well with mixer on high. Cook at 350° in tube pan until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
This bakes better if started in cold oven.

title: teisen cymraeg(ta'son kim rag)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend in lard as you would for pie crust.
Whisk eggs and milk together and add to mixture.
Fold in currants.
Cover and put in icebox (refrigerate for a few hours).

title: orange raisin cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs. Beat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cream cheese frosting.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Enjoy!!

title: cousin faye's sleepy time turkey
directions: I have done this without putting flour in the bag with fine results.
To be done the night before serving.

title: rascal's cheese potato puff
directions: Place potatoes in a large kettle.
Cover with water.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook until tender.
Drain.
Mash potatoes until smooth.

title: chile relleno casserole
directions: Spray 11 x 13-inch glass dish with Pam.
Layer chiles on bottom of pan.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Blend milk, eggs and flour. Pour over cheese and chiles.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven, add Jack cheese and top with tomato sauce.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Let set for 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: forever ambers
directions: Combine the orange slices, milk, coconut, pecans and orange extract.
Mix together; pour into baking dish.
Bake at 300° until bubbly, then stir in confectioners sugar.
Drop with a spoon onto waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: linda's lasagna
directions: Boil lasagna noodles. Simmer meats and onion and drain. Add tomato products, spices and ketchup. Simmer until sauce like. In 9 x 13-inch pan, assemble sauce mixture, noodles, sauce mixture, all types of cheeses and repeat. Bake at 325° until cheese is golden brown (uncovered).

title: caramel corn
directions: You will also need 1 brown paper grocery bag.

title: deep pan peach pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix well together the sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour batter over melted butter. Do not stir.
Pour sweetened peaches over batter.
Do not stir. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: colby corn chowder
directions: Place potatoes in a Dutch oven.
Sprinkle with salt and cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Meanwhile, in a skillet, saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in corn and bacon.
Heat through. Drain potatoes.
Add milk.
Heat through.
Stir in corn mixture and cheese.
Serve immediately.
Serves 12 to 14 (3 quarts).

title: avocado and tomato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Mix oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Pour over avocados.
Toss; stir in bacon, tomato and onion.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Just before serving, place on salad greens with slotted spoon.

title: persimmon pie
directions: Mix everything together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix well and roll.
Put rolls in waxed paper.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 to 48 hours.
Take out and slice.
Bake in cookie pan about 13 to 15 minutes at 350°, until light brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix 1 cup of flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and pudding.
Add mashed banana and milk.
Beat with mixer until blended and then for 2 more minutes.
Add in eggs and the other 3/4 cup of flour.
(mix) Add nuts (stir in with spoon).
Bake in loaf pan about 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack for 5 minutes then remove from pan and continue cooling on wire rack.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 3 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
(Toothpick in center should come out clean.)

title: special sourdough rye
directions: Mix a sponge of first 4 ingredients.
To this sponge add remaining ingredients.
Set in a warm place for 8 to 24 hours, depending on the sourness desired.
An ideal place to set this sponge would be by a pilot light.
Dough should be frothy.
Stir well.
Turn out on a floured surface and knead for 10 minutes, adding an additional 1/2 to 3/4 cup flour a little at a time, as dough becomes sticky.
Shape into 2 loaves (oval or round) and place on a greased cookie sheet and cover with plastic wrap.
Set in a warm place to rise until double in bulk.
Brush with 1 egg yolk, beaten with 1 tablespoon water.
Slash tops of loaves with a sharp knife.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pans immediately and cool before cutting.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Form into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes in 300° oven.
While hot, roll in additional confectioners sugar.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter each biscuit.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in a bag.
Shake quartered biscuits, 5 or 6 at a time, in the bag.
Place in ungreased Bundt pan.
Melt margarine; add remaining sugar and cinnamon to margarine.
Bring to a boil to melt sugar; pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Flip right away onto plate.

title: wild plum liqueur
directions: Dissolve sugar in vodka.
Put in a glass jar with plums and cover with a towel or Saran Wrap.
Punch a few holes in Saran Wrap so it can breathe.
Leave for 8 to 10 weeks.
Never stir.
Plums will darken and become hard as aging takes place.
Strain and chill.

title: seafood enchiladas
directions: Mix 2 soups and salsa. Set aside. Beat together cream cheese and sour cream. Stir in crab meat, 1/2 cup Monterey Jack, 1/2 cup Mexican blend, 4 chopped onions onions and chillies. Spray each tortilla with olive oil spray and heat 1 minute on each side. Place crab mixture into each and roll. Place seam side down in 13 x 9 dish with 1 cup of reserved soup mix in bottom of the dish. Pour remaining soup mix over tortillas and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle on remaining cheeses and bake 10 more minutes.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Put eggs, mustard, cream of tartar and lemon juice in blender pitcher.
Blend 1 to 2 minutes until light yellow in color.
Do not turn blender off; slowly drizzle in 1 cup oil.
Blend until it looks thick.
Refrigerate promptly.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook and drain	squash and onions.
Beat eggs.	Combine with soup, salt	and
cheese.
Put in buttered casserole bowl. Pour bread crumbs on top.

title: fish fillets with mushrooms
directions: Arrange fish fillets in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch microproof baking dish with the thick edges toward the outside of dish.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle
all remaining ingredients over top.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook on maximum power for 5 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.

title: chex party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Heat butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish in oven until butter is melted.
Remove dish.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt.
Mix.
Add cereals, nuts and pretzels to butter mixture.
Mix until all pieces are coated. Heat in oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper towels and let cool.
Makes about 9 cups.

title: apple walnut coffeecake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients and blend well.
Spoon into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: taco beef noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown beef and onion. Stir in sauce, water and seasoning mix.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
In large bowl, combine cottage cheese, sour cream, flour and bouillon; mix well.
Add noodles, green onion and pepper; blend well.
Spoon noodle mixture into well greased 2-quart baking dish; top with meat mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes; sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Bake 2 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients
in order.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: nana's chicken puffs
directions: Heat oil and lightly saute chicken breasts.
Do not brown. Sprinkle each breast with rosemary and garlic salt.
Roll each pastry shell into a circle about 7 to 9-inches in diameter.
Place chicken on half of each pastry.
Spread each piece of chicken with one piece of chive cheese.
Fold pastry over chicken and seal edges.
Place on baking sheet.
Place in 450° preheated oven and immediately reduce heat to 400°.
Bake uncovered about 30 minutes or until golden.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cook cream, egg yolks and vanilla, stirring all the time, until thickened.
Cool, then add whipping cream that is whipped, grapes, marshmallows and pineapple.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.

title: oriental marinade
directions: Mix together and use to marinate meat or poultry.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: bacon and water chestnut roll-ups(appetizer)
directions: Marinate water chestnuts in vinegar for about 30 minutes.
Cut bacon slices in half.
Mix brown sugar and mustard.
Coat each piece of bacon on both sides with mixture.
Wrap water chestnut in bacon.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Place on a rack and bake in slow oven at 275° for 20 minutes or until crisp.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Place each piece of chicken between 2 sheets of waxed paper; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness with meat mallet.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Remove chicken; drain on paper towels.
Keep warm.
Add lemon juice and lemon slices to pan drippings in skillet.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Pour lemon mixture over chicken and sprinkle with parsley.
Yields 6 servings.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix in order the flour, baking soda, cream of tartar, brown sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Refrigerate overnight.
Let stand and slice off.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Fry bacon; drain and crumble into pie shell.
Cook chopped onion in bacon grease until brown; drain and add to pie shell.
Spoon thawed spinach into shell and top with shredded cheese.
Mix together eggs, cream, milk and seasonings and pour over pie fillings.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, reduce heat to 300° and continue baking about 45 minutes or until knife inserted halfway from center to edge comes out clean.

title: tangy orange jello
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add thawed orange juice.
Drain mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Mix with Jell-O.
Pour all into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Allow to set, then top with 1 large package pudding mixed with 1 cup milk.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with ground nuts.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Sauce:
Clean garlic cloves.
Heat olive oil to bubbling and add pressed garlic.
Stir until brown.
Add minced clams and juice to the browned garlic.
Cook until juice boils.

title: baked beans
directions: Cover the beans with cold water; soak overnight.
In the morning, add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Put into a bean pot or large Dutch oven and completely cover the beans with water.
Bake in a 325° oven with the cover on for several hours until beans are done.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together in microwave oven for 1 1/2 minutes.
Place Rice Chex in bowl and pour microwave mix on top. Stir until evenly coated.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core
and slice thinly 8 apples.	Sprinkle with a little lemon juice
and
1/2 cup sugar.
Pour in pie pan.	Mix brown sugar
and	flour and pour over apple mixture.
Dot with butter. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Start adding the flour mixture and buttermilk alternately, beating well after each addition.
Add mashed bananas, flavoring and chopped pecans and fold into batter, mixing well.
Pour batter into 3 (9-inch) round cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tester inserted into middle of cake comes out clean.
Remove from oven.
Let cool 10 minutes before removing from pans to finish cooling.
Frost with German Chocolate Cake Filling.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips.
Place layer potato chips in large baking dish.
Cover with chicken mixture. Top with remaining potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels in top of double boiler with cream.
Stir until smooth.
Put a spoonful on top of pecans on greased cookie sheet. Cool.
Pour melted chocolate chips on top.
I usually use semi-sweet chips but you can mix with sweet chocolate chips. Makes a nice gift.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Line ungreased cookie sheet with roll dough (stretch to fit pan).
Bake 11 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Combine cream cheese, mayo and dry Ranch mix.
Spread over cooled crust.
Refrigerate.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Add cooked and drained turkey.
Add remaining ingredients, except noodles and Cheddar cheese.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour a little sauce in bottom of baking dish (9 x 13-inches).
Top with cooked noodles.
Layer sauce on bottom, then noodles and sauce, then noodles and sauce.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: hector's favorite flan(baked custard)
directions: Caramelize sugar in skillet on top of stove.
(Heat until it turns brown.)
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Cook
rice
with
margarine by package directions.
Mix corn, cheese and soup together.
Add rice mixture.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sour cream in boiling water.
Add fruit cocktail, oranges and marshmallows.
Chill until ready to eat.

title: molded pineapple cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Crush cranberries with a fork and add.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart mold. Refrigerate.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix cream cheese with sugar.
Mix Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Dissolve marshmallows.
Add cream cheese and sugar.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: 40 clove chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken and potatoes. Roll chicken in mixture. Place into baking pan and add all of oil mixture and potatoes. Cook, covered, 25 minutes. Turn chicken and continue cooking until done.

title: eggplant parmigiana(yields 2 servings)
directions: Pour melted butter into a 10 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Combine cornflake crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper; stir well and set aside.

title: jordan marsh blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Fold in 2 1/2 cups blueberries.
Pour into muffin tin.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Pat in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs on high speed of electric mixer until light, about 4 minutes.
Add powdered sugar, softened butter and vanilla, beat 5 minutes.
Spread over crumbs.
Chill 30 minutes. Spread pineapple over creamed mixture.
Arrange bananas over pineapple.
Cover with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with pecans. Cover; refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Garnish with cherries. Makes 12 servings.

title: boiled spice cake
directions: Put all of the above ingredients in a saucepan. Boil. Remove from heat and cool. Add 2 teaspoons baking soda and 3 cups flour. Mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13 cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: family-style salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon and reserve liquid.
Flake the salmon and set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan, then add onion and green pepper and saute for 10 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Remove from heat and stir in the reserved salmon liquid.
Cook over low heat until mixture leaves sides of pan, stirring constantly.
Beat in the potatoes, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce, then stir in the salmon.
Cool, then chill thoroughly.
Shape into croquettes. Beat the egg with the milk, then dip the croquettes in the egg mixture and coat thoroughly with the crumbs.
Fry in deep fat at 365° for about 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup with one can milk into baking dish. Add 2 drained cans of tuna. Mix together. Crumble potato chips into mixture. Stir together. Pour a layer of potato chips over top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, 1 cup flour, cornstarch and salt in a double boiler; add the boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cook over boiling water until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Beat egg yolks with 1/2 cup sugar and gradually pour hot mixture over them, while stirring.
Return to double boiler and cook 5 minutes longer. Just before removing from heat, add lemon juice and rind.
Mix well; cool and pour into pie shell.
To brown meringue, bake in a slow oven at 300° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool, away from drafts.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix and pour over cake mix on the bottom layer.
Top with topping.

title: pink champagne dessert
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar well.
Add remaining ingredients, then fold in Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: brer rabbit molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg; beat well.
Add molasses, then add dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Chill overnight. Form into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place on sprayed sheet; flatten and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: marinade vegetable salad
directions: Drain cans of ingredients and put together vegetables.
In saucepan, combine sugar, oil, water, salt, pepper and white vinegar.
Heat until sugar is melted.
Do not boil.
Pour this mixture over vegetables and let stand at least 24 hours.
Makes enough for 12.

title: spicy bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar, spice, salt, milk and vanilla. Heat 1 3/4 cups milk; stir into egg mixture.
Blend in bread crumbs; mix well.
Turn into buttered 1-quart casserole.
Place in pan of hot water.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix shortening into dry ingredients with pastry blender.
Mix together vinegar, cold water and egg.
Add to first mixture.
This makes 1 single and 1 double crust.
It keeps in refrigerator several weeks.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix well and chill dough several hours or overnight.
Flour hands and roll into small balls.
Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Leave good space between as dough will spread.
Bake at 300° to 325°.
Watch closely, they brown quickly.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add oil and beat well.
Add flour and other dry ingredients.
Beat.
Add vanilla and pumpkin mix and beat slowly.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together, then add dry ingredients, nuts and raisins.
Pour batter into greased and floured bread pan; bake for 1 hour.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Blend soups and broth; stir in processed cheese.
Mix with spaghetti, turkey and mushrooms.
Turn into greased 11 1/2 x 7 3/8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 30 minutes, until bubbly and browned.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: crab stuffed eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks; mash and combine with remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Just before serving, stuff egg whites with crab meat mixture.
Makes 12 halves with extra stuffing to use as a sandwich spread.

title: mammaw's buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening in a mixing bowl, either by mixer or by hand.
Add the egg yolks, one at a time and blend good after each addition.
Add flavoring.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to first mixture, alternately with buttermilk (begin and end with flour).
Beat egg whites and fold into batter last.
Pour batter in a 10-inch tube pan or two loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
May need to bake a little longer.
Be sure top of cake is brown and firm.
Cool and remove from pan.
(May use nutmeg, if you do not have lemon or orange extract.)

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook hamburger in a skillet.
Add enchilada sauce.
In 8 x 13-inch cake pan, layer hamburger mixture, grated cheese, soup and crushed Doritos, twice.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: molasses corn balls
directions: Boil
ingredients
until
mixture
becomes brittle when tried in	cold water.
Remove from heat.	Add a pinch of soda to lighten
mixture.
Set pan in cold water to cool a little. Pour over corn.	Mix well.
Form into balls.
Slightly butter hands to avoid sticking.

title: hot peach tea
directions: Mix all together thoroughly.
Store in an airtight container. Use 3 or 4 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.
Stir to dissolve. This is wonderful on a cold day.

title: rhubarb drink
directions: Cook rhubarb
and
water and strain.
Add pineapple juice, sugar and cherry jello.
Put in jars and cold pack for 10 minutes. Add water to taste when serving.
Also ginger ale if desired.

title: microwave fluffy muffins
directions: In mixing bowl stir flour with sugar, baking powder and salt. Make a well in center of dry mixture.
Combine eggs, oil and milk. Add all at once to dry ingredients and stir just to
moisten. Fill paper-lined microwave containers 1/2 full.
Microwave 1/2 to 1 minute for each muffin at Medium-high (No. 7).
Check for doneness with toothpick.

title: heavenly jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice.
Pour over jello; stir until completely dissolved.
Set aside to cool.
When cool and beginning to thicken, add cheese, tidbits and nuts.
Mix well by hand, then fold in whipping cream (not whipped).
Pour into mold or bowl and refrigerate until set.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple cake and icing
directions: Stir all ingredients together well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done, about 40 minutes.
Frost with icing.

title: caramel-orange rolls
directions: Combine sugar, orange rind, orange juice, mace and margarine. Spread over the bottom of ungreased shallow pan.
Place rolls upside down over sugar mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven.
Let rolls stand in pan until syrup thickens, or about 1 minute.
Invert pan and remove rolls so the caramel-orange topping coats rolls.
Yield:
12 rolls.
Approximate calories/serving:

title: crisscross pickles
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and put 2 trays ice cubes over and let set 3 hours.
Bring to boil; add cukes and heat for 5 minutes. Bottle.

title: hawaiian galore
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add pineapple.
Cook until thick; let cool.
Slice 3 bananas in bottom of pie shells.
Put 1/2 cup coconut and 2/3 cup pecans on top of bananas.
Pour filling over this and top with Cool Whip or desired topping. Makes 2 pies.

title: western meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in loaf pan and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Make into 2 rolls 2-inches in diameter.
Place in refrigerator for 1/2 hour or longer.
Slice and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: cheese grits souffle
directions: In saucepan, combine water and salt; bring to full boil. Gradually add grits to boiling water, stirring constantly.
Return to boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 2 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until very thick.
Stir in butter or margarine; set aside.

title: cheeseless cheesecake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/4 cup of the water (you can do this in microwave oven on High for 30 seconds; don't scorch.) Add everything in blender.
Blend 4 or 5 minutes in blender.
Pour in graham cracker crust and refrigerate.
Top with cherry pie filling.
One-quarter serving = 1 milk and 1 fruit.

title: aunt peg's crab cakes
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients until celery and onion are tender. Remove from heat to cool slightly.
Mix remaining ingredients. (Be sure to squeeze water out of bread.)
Add margarine mixture; mix.
Make patties and fry in oil or margarine until brown.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Grate graham crackers until resembles crumbs or use in food processor. Put cream and marshmallows in large pot on low until marshmallows are melted. Add raisins, pecans, coconut, candied cherries and candied pineapple. Mix well and pack fruit cake in graham cracker box. Let sit in freezer for 12 hours. When serving, take out of freezer and serve. Whatever is left, put back in freezer. Can be kept in freezer up to a year.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain and rinse.
Put in a large serving bowl.
Mix oil, soy, lemon juice and 10 drops of Tabasco sauce.
Add oil mixture to pasta.
Toss well.
Chop all vegetables.
Add to pasta. Toss again.
Add more Tabasco sauce, if needed.
Let sit three hours or overnight.
Great to take on a picnic.

title: mama's best chili
directions: Cook the ground beef in an extra large pan until done. Drain the grease. Add all other ingredients. Cover and simmer on low heat for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally. If needed, add extra water or	tomato sauce. Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Boil strawberries and box of jello (do not add water) and let cool.
Mix together milk, pudding and sour cream.
Layer a trifle dish with vanilla wafers.
Add a layer of pudding mix then a layer of the strawberry mixture then a layer of cool whip.
Continue to layer till ingredients are used.

title: quick mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion and sprinkle with garlic salt in large skillet.
Drain and add tomatoes, beef, bouillon, broth, corn, rice and chili powder.
Heat to boiling point.
Remove from heat.
Stir and cover.
Ready to eat in 10 minutes.
May substitute regular rice, cooked, for Minute rice and water.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Blend all ingredients well; pour over meat.
Marinate 24 hours in refrigerator, then grill the meat.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of boiling salted water for 10 minutes.
When tender, drain and set aside.
Melt margarine in medium skillet.
Add sugar and honey; blend.
Add carrots; cook 3 or 4 minutes over low heat, stirring so each carrot is glazed. Sprinkle with mint.
Substitute parsley for fresh mint, if preferred.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet dill refrigerator pickles
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, water and salt.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
In a large nonmetallic container, combine cucumbers, onion and dill.
Pour dressing over; cool. Cover and refrigerate at least 3 days before serving.
Stir occasionally.
Yields 3 1/2 quarts.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Combine milk and broth.
Melt butter in large pan (big enough for everything).
Add onions and cook until tender.
Stir in flour.
Add milk mixture, slowly stirring with wire whip to mix well.

title: mint chocolate cream puffs
directions: Spray a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Set aside. In a small saucepan, combine water and margarine.
Bring to boiling.
Add flour all at once, stirring vigorously.
Cook and stir until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Remove from heat.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition with a wooden spoon until mixture is shiny and smooth.
Drop mixture into 8 mounds 3 inches apart on the baking sheet.

title: burgundy beef tips with mushrooms
directions: Remove all fiber from the tenderloin and cut into 1-inch strips.
Place beef in preheated skillet (375°) and stir the meat until brown on all sides.
Add 1/2 cup wine, water, bouillon cubes, onion soup mix, and 1/2 can mushrooms.
Simmer the mixture until the meat is tender, about 45 minutes.
Just before serving, add 1/2 cup wine and 1/2 can mushrooms.
Serve beef tips over rice.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and syrup in medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs and vanilla, stirring well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Make cake.
Cool cake, then split in layers.

title: banana split cake
directions: In a large cake pan, melt the butter. Blend in the graham crackers.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, egg yolks, flour, milk, butter and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° and bake for about 25 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Remove from oven and top with meringue.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together and beat.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook peeled potatoes, cut into small pieces.
Add all other ingredients, partially mash potatoes.
Add water to make right thickness.

title: southern sausage casserole
directions: Peel potatoes
and cut into thin slices.
Place half of the slices
into
the
bottom
of
a buttered casserole dish. Cover with sausage, shaped into 4 patties.
Add thickly sliced apples and
sprinkle
with salt.
Cover with remaining potato slices
and brush
with water.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: chicken paillards with marsala and mushrooms
directions: Flatten chicken breasts; sprinkle generously with pepper.
Heat 1/2 oil in large skillet; saute 1/2 of chicken.
Repeat until all are done.
Keep chicken warm in low oven.
Melt butter in same skillet.
Cook mushrooms with a pinch of salt.
Saute mushrooms until all the moisture evaporates.
Add shallots, garlic, Marsala and chicken stock; bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes. Reduce heat.
Add light cream slowly until desired consistency is achieved.
Serve chicken on bed of pasta; cover generously with mushrooms and sauce.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken; debone and cut into small pieces.
Mix flour, pepper and margarine.
Add milk; mix well.
Roll out thin.
Cut in strips.
Drop dumplings in the 2 quarts of boiling chicken broth. (I use a little more than 2 quarts.)
Cook 10 minutes uncovered and 5 minutes covered.
(Add salt and pepper to chicken while boiling.)

title: peanut-butter fudge
directions: Slowly add milk as stirring first four ingredients.
Stir all ingredients together, then turn heat on high until it comes to a boil.
Then turn heat to medium and cool until it forms a little ball on cold water (stirring constantly).
Then turn off heat and add the peanut butter and marshmallows.
Remove from stove and stir vigorously until the fudge begins to harden.
Put in a cake square container, level the fudge with a knife.
Let cool for about 20 minutes, then put in refrigerator to set up.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies "no bake"
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Cook 1 minute after it starts boiling. Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well and drop on wax paper.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water together until it reaches hard ball (250°).
Beat egg whites and salt at high speed for 3 minutes.
Pour syrup slowly into beaten whites while beating at a high speed.
Continue beating until mixture forms a peak when beater is raised.
Sometimes this takes 10 minutes or longer.

title: coconut-squash pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and add to squash.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Place chicken in a Dutch oven; cover with water and cook until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken and debone.
Reserve 1/2 cup of broth.
Combine soups in saucepan.
Add canned milk and bring to a slow boil.
Just heat until soups are heated.
Combine stuffing mix, butter and 1/2 cup broth.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing mix in a 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan.
Layer chicken over the stuffing mix and pour soup mixture over chicken.
Top with remaining stuffing mixture. Bake uncovered at 350° or until golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: The best pie recipe is on the can of Libby's pumpkin.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan; cool.

title: spicy breakfast treats
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package directions. Fill 24 paper-lined muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Put melted butter in a small bowl. In another small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon. Dip tops of warm muffins first in melted butter and then in sugar-cinnamon mixture.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and continue creaming until light.
Sift flour, baking soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt together and add alternately with cream to creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins or nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheets.
Bake in moderately hot oven (375°) for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 36 cookies.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Set jello as directed on box; set aside to cool.
Grind oranges, nuts, apples and cranberries.
Mix with jello.
Add sugar. May need more sugar.
Sweeten to taste.

title: green chili
directions: Saute pork cubes lightly.
Add chopped green chilies and garlic powder.
Add water.
Simmer for two hours, adding water as needed.
Thicken with flour and water paste until it is the consistency of white sauce.
Serve as smothering on bean burritos. Melt Cheddar cheese on top of burrito after smothering.

title: "cheese souffle"
directions: Scald in double boiler until cheese is melted, then add 3 well beaten egg yolks.
Allow to cool before adding 3 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Fold in lightly . Bake 40 minutes in moderate oven.

title: joann's ice cream pie
directions: Melt butter in dish.
Crush entire bag of cookies.
Mix together and bake at 350° for approximately 8 minutes.
Cool completely.
Soften ice cream and spread on cooled crust.
Top with swirls of topping.
Freeze for 24 hours.

title: chicken and marinade
directions: In shallow bowl, mix lemon juice, celery salt, garlic juice, pepper, sour cream, Worcestershire sauce and paprika.
Place chicken in marinade.
Cover and place in refrigerator for 3 hours or overnight.

title: pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place roast in a deep roasting pan.

title: jam filled muffins
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, melted butter and milk.
Add flour, baking powder, lemon peel and salt. Blend well.
Use 12 count muffin tin lined with paper cupcake holders.
Fill with 1/2 the batter, add a tablespoon of jam, then add batter to fill cup.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine jello, hot water and cold water.
Refrigerate for 1 hour, just to jell.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: okra patties
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add only enough water to make stiff enough to make into patties.
Fry until brown.
Very good.

title: sesame green beans
directions: Trim ends from green beans.
If very long, cut in half.
In small saucepan over medium heat, toast sesame seed until golden brown, stirring and shaking saucepan frequently.
Remove from heat.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Melt stick of butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar on melted butter.
Put pineapple slices on top of melted mix.
Decorate with cherry and/or pecan halves.
Pour cake mixture on top.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease
2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs, oil and sugar.
Add vanilla and zucchini.
Mix well.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add to zucchini mixture.
add nuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: porquitos guacamole
directions: Brown pork, onions and garlic.
Add green chilies, water, cumin, oregano, salt and pepper; simmer for 1 hour.
Wrap tortillas in foil and warm in oven to soften.
Roll filling inside tortillas.
Fry until light brown and crispy on the outside.
Keep warm in oven while you make the topping.

title: enchilada's
directions: Fry hamburger, drain and set aside.
Put olives, onions and cheese in separate bowls.
Have two large, heavy frypans on stove. In one have hot oil and in the other hot enchilada sauce.
Fry tortillas 1 or 2 seconds in oil; then into hot sauce.
Remove to board and stuff with meat, olives, cheese and onions.
Roll and place in oblong pan, close together.
Sprinkle with any remaining cheese over top.
Pour remaining sauce over all.
Garnish with whole olives.
Bake at 350° until good and hot.
May be frozen for future use.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to instructions.
Add pecans and 1/2 of coconut.
Bake cake.
Mix milk and cream of coconut.
Punch holes in	warm
cake
and
pour
mixture over cake.
Let cool. Spread Cool Whip over cake and add coconut.

title: raspberry wine cooler
directions: Combine raspberries and liqueur.
Let set 1 hour; strain.
Add wine and ginger ale.
Serve cold.

title: peachtree fuzzy navel cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in covered container for 24 hours. Mix rest of ingredients together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes in Bundt pan.

title: gramma ginny's rotini salad
directions: Cook rotini; drain.
Add bottle of dressing and package of dressing mix. Stir in cucumbers and tomatoes.
Stir well.
Chill at least 1 hour and serve.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar thoroughly; add almond extract.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Mix gradually into butter mixture.
Stir in almonds.

title: coconut pie(my mother's recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Pour in a 9-inch pie plate, greased.
Makes its own crust.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes or until custard is set.
Serve cold.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in milk until smooth. Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla. Pour into crust. Chill 3 hours or until set. Top with pie filling before serving.

title: monster munch snack
directions: You will need a brown grocery bag.

title: ranch cheese wafers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, cayenne pepper and salt in a large bowl. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Mix in cheese. Fold in cereal or nuts. Form dough into 1-inch rounds.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten to 1 3/4-inch rounds, using back of fork.
Bake until light brown, 15 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: cabbage bean soup
directions: Saute onion in a large nonstick pan (spray with Pam) for about 3 minutes.
Halve carrots and celery and then slice crosswise. Add to pan with onion, sauteing slowly over low heat for about 2 minutes.
Stir in water, cabbage and sugar.
Simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes with juice and break up tomatoes. Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add beans and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes until heated through.
Only 1 gram fat per serving.

title: red hot pickle rings
directions: Cover
rings
with
lime
and
water
mixture.	Soak 24 hours. Drain
and
wash
in
cold water.	Soak 3 hours in ice water. Drain.
Mix
cup vinegar, food color and alum; pour over
rings with
water
to
cover.
Heat and simmer 2 hours; drain.
Bring 2
cups
vinegar,
cups	water, sugar, stick cinnamon and red hots to boil and pour over rings.
Weigh down to
keep all covered with mixture.
Let stand overnight.
Heat 3 mornings; the 3rd morning heat to boiling and pack into jars and seal.

title: wendell's chicken stew
directions: Prepare ingredients and simmer together.
Serve with crackers or cornbread.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill overnight or for several hours.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar, salt and vinegar together until ready to eat.
Mix cucumbers and onions together.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Combine pie filling and cinnamon and extract.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Drizzle with butter. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° about 35 minutes.

title: clover blossom wine
directions: Pour boiling water over clover blossoms.
Cover tight, let stand 3 days.
Add oranges and lemon, cut up, peels and all.
Add sugar; cook 15 minutes.
Remove from heat, let cool enough to add yeast.
Cover tight for 1 week then strain and bottle.

title: club cracker cookies
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil sugar, brown sugar, milk and oleo for 2 minutes.
Layer Club crackers on bottom of pan.
Pour mixture over bottom layer.
Repeat layer of Club crackers.
Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Spread over top.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut and enjoy!

title: frosty lime fizz
directions: Put pineapple juice, lime juice and sugar in blender.
Spoon half of sherbet in blender.
Adjust lid; blend until ingredients are smooth.
Pour 1/2 cup of this mixture into each fo 6 (12 ounce) glasses.
Add additional scoop of sherbet to each glass.
Fill each glass with carbonated beverage.
Serves 6.
This can also be served from punch bowl as punch.

title: granny's dewberry cream pie
directions: Line 1
unbaked
pie
shell with 1 cup fruit.
Then mix the following
and
pour
over fruit:
eggs, sugar, flour, Pet milk and salt.
Crumble topping over pie.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: muffins
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over cereal; mix thoroughly.
Add oil and brown sugar; mix again.
Add the buttermilk, eggs, soda and salt (optional); work in flour gradually.
Cover; let stand in refrigerator.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: christmas cheese logs
directions: Mix with approximately 1/2 small can Pet milk.
Roll into several small rolls.
Sprinkle wax paper with paprika and roll cheese rolls.

title: easy, tasty green beans
directions: Put green beans with juice in pan.
Add bouillon cube and sprinkle generously with dry minced onion.
Simmer on top of stove for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: fettuccine bake
directions: Brown meat in ovenproof skillet and drain. Add onion. Cook until tender. Stir in tomatoes and oregano. Bring to a boil, then simmer 20 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in Mozzarella. Sprinkle Parmesan over tomato mixture. Toss noodles with remaining ingredients and spread over Parmesan.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan to cover noodles.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Brown together beef, onion and bell pepper.
Place into crock-pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: vegetable and cheese casserole
directions: Warm
or
steam vegetables until defrosted and softened. Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: light biscuits
directions: Bake at 475° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: salmon dill canapes
directions: Toast bread.
Mix cream cheese, dill and lemon juice.
Spread on toast.
Top with a fine slice of salmon. Garnish each canape with a sprig of dill.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown ground round; saute onion in same pan and drain.
Shred roast beef and cook in same pan until gravy is gone.
In separate pot, heat 2 tablespoons bacon grease, then stir in refried beans. Stir thoroughly, then add ground round/onion and roast beef to beans and mix well until mixture is thoroughly heated.
Place meat/bean mixture in ungreased baking dish.
Spread diced chilies over mixture.
Spread diced black olives over green chilies.
Layer top with both cheeses.
Drizzle top with taco sauce.
Place in preheated 350° oven until cheese is thoroughly melted.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Add optional items as desired and serve with chips.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: warm hug
directions: This drink can be made virgin by leaving out the brandy.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Serve over roast or with a sandwich or chicken or ribs.

title: refrigerator cukes
directions: This will keep several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: french chicken
directions: Simmer chicken until meat falls off bone.
Cool and cut up. Cook tomatoes, onions, garlic, peppers and mushrooms until mushy.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions in a 9 x 13 inch pan. Cool 10 minutes, leave cake in pan.
Use wooden spoon end, poke holes in cake approximately 1 1/2 inch apart.
Drizzle caramel ice cream topping on top and in all holes.
Drizzle sweetened condensed milk on top and in all holes.
Let stand 2 minutes. Spread icing on top.
Break up the candy bars.
Sprinkle candy bar pieces on top of icing.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; knead last cup of flour.
Make into a roll; leave in refrigerator overnight.
Slice and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: easy chocolate fudge(microwave)
directions: Melt chips and milk in microwave on High 3 minutes.
Add nuts and vanilla, mixing well.
Pour in a foil-lined 8-inch square pan. Chill.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas.
Mix well. Add sour milk, dry ingredients and nuts.
Beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients.
Put into graham cracker crust; top with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well. Carefully stir in potatoes.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and corn flakes.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: hot toddy, chocolate
directions: Heat milk; add chocolate.
Stir well.
Blend in coffee flavoring.
Serve hot.
Makes 1 serving, 202 calories.

title: pineapple slush
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender; process until smooth.

title: salt and pepper steak
directions: Cut the steak into very thin slices.
In a skillet with a lid, heat the oil and add steak slices.
Cook, uncovered, until browned. Pour out some of the oil and add the remaining ingredients except the rice.
Cover and cook for 30 to 35 minutes until the juice has thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: lori's pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini.
Cook turkey bacon until crisp; crumble when cool.
Mix rotini, mushrooms, tomatoes and broccoli.
Pour 3/4 bottle of dressing over this.
Pour 1/2 bottle of dressing over carrots in separate bowl and cover.
When ready to serve, mix together and pour rest of dressing over salad.
Add turkey bacon.

title: meatballs over noodles
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Shape into small meatballs. Place in electric frypan and brown on all sides.
Mix together the soup, sour cream and milk.
Pour over meatballs and simmer for 25 minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: pepper steak
directions: Combine flour and seasonings.
Pound into meat with meat hammer or edge of heavy saucer.
In skillet brown meat in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add soup and ketchup.

title: easy dip
directions: Mix well. Chill. Serve with Fritos.

title: spaghetti-chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done; I grill mine.
Cook spaghetti; drain. Layer in large casserole dish: sauce, spaghetti, chicken, sauce, then cheese.
I do 2 layers, then bake
35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sauteed snap beans
directions: Saute beans 1 minute in enough oil or bacon fat to cover bottom of wok or pan.
Add instant onion and water to mix and saute again. Add dash of garlic salt, cracked black pepper and chili sauce. Toss lightly.
Serve on platter.
Garnish with beets or other vegetable of your choice to add color.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Combine eggs, oil and strawberries.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing well.
Pour batter into two greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Poke holes in bread with toothpicks.
Mix juice from strawberries and sugar to taste.
Pour over bread while still warm.
Allow to set 24 hours.

title: john's pancakes
directions: Two tablespoons snow equals 1 egg.

title: oysters rockefeller en casserole
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in bowl and cook on High for 3 minutes or until thickened.
Stir twice.
Spread spinach in 2-quart casserole (be sure you defrost and drain).
Pour the stew mixture over spinach.
Arrange oysters on top (be sure to pierce with a toothpick each oyster several times).
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and butter and put on top of oysters. Sprinkle paprika.
Cook uncovered at High for 5 minutes.
Cover and cook 5 minutes more on High.
Let stand 5 minutes covered. Remove bay leaf from casserole before serving.
Serves 4 people.

title: apple and blue cheese slaw
directions: In a large bowl, mix well cream, oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and paprika.
Add cabbage, cubed apples, celery and cheese; toss to mix well.
Garnish with apple wedges.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cube steaks saute
directions: Heat oil in large (12-inch skillet) over moderate-high heat. Season steaks with salt and pepper.
Saute steaks until browned, about 1 to 2 minutes on each side.
Reduce heat to moderate.
Stir in beef broth and horseradish and bring to a boil.
Serve immediately.

title: helen byrd's wedding punch
directions: *If strawberry Kool-Aid, only use 1 package.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Cool.
Chop up vegetables and meat. Mix spaghetti, vegetables, meat, salad dressing and seasoning.
Mix well and serve warm or cold.
Best when served cold.

title: citrus marmalade
directions: Position a knife blade in a food processor bowl; add orange. Pulse 8 times or until orange is finely chopped.
Spoon orange into a 2-quart glass measure.
Add sugar and lemon juice; stir well. Microwave at High 17 to 21 minutes or until thickened, stirring every 3 minutes.
(Mixture will continue to thicken as it cools.) Let cool.
Store in an airtight container in refrigerator up to 1 week.
Yield:
2 cups (serving size is 1 tablespoon).

title: sausage dressing
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Cook onion and celery in butter or margarine until tender.
Mix stuffing, poultry seasoning, salt and black pepper.
Stir in broth, celery, onion, butter and sausage. Mix well.
Stuff 14 to 20 pound turkey lightly.
Do not overstuff.
Dressing may be baked separately in an uncovered dish for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: best ever sugar cookies
directions: Combine margarine, vegetable oil and sugars in a large mixing bowl; beat well using electric mixer at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in vanilla. Combine remaining ingredients in another bowl; add gradually to creamed mixture, beating well.

title: fruit sauce
directions: Whisk cornstarch into water, orange juice and lemon juice. Heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add nutmeg and sweetener, if desired.
Serve hot over whole wheat pancakes or chill and serve with fresh fruit.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 4 cups.

title: chicken luau
directions: Place chicken, skin side up, in shallow 9 X 13 baking dish. Slowly cook pineapple in butter for 5 minutes.
Add cornstarch, salt, pepper, and cayenne pepper.
Stir in broth and pineapple juice.
Add marmalade, sherry, chutney, celery and spices.
Mix well.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender. Sprinkle almonds over chicken.
Garnish with green pepper strips, if desired.
Serve with rice pilaf.
Yield:
6-8 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini slices in boiling, salted water until tender. Drain.
In saucepan, melt butter (5 tablespoons).
Add carrots and onions; saute.
Remove from heat and add 2 cups bread crumbs and remaining ingredients.
Fold in zucchini.
Spoon into 3-quart casserole.
Melt remaining butter and add to dish.
Sprinkle with remaining bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add Miracle Whip last.

title: ricotta pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together until blended well.
Beat eggs last and mix in all ingredients.
Bake in glass, ungreased dish in 375° oven for 10 minutes, then drop temperature down to 350° for about 60 minutes.
When pie is golden brown on top, it is done. Let cool, then refrigerate until cold.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix and cook rice with 2 cups of milk, gently and slowly so the rice and milk do not burn.
While cooking, stir slowly and add the condensed milk bit by bit.
If the rice does not expand, add more milk as needed.
Sprinkle cinnamon to taste when the rice is tender.
Rice should be left moist.
Serves 6.
May be served warm or chilled.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Bake for 3 to 4 hours at 325°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: fool 'em every time lemon cake
directions: Prepare a yellow cake mix according to package directions and bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass baking dish (greased and floured). While cake is baking, mix powdered sugar with bottled lemon juice (mixture will be thin).
When cake is done, while it's hot, carefully poke holes all over top of cake with fork.
Pour icing mixture evenly over cake.

title: caramel nut slices(refrigerator cookies)
directions: Mix well shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Stir in.
Add nuts.
Shape into 2 rolls, 2-inches across.
Chill.
Cut in slices 1/8-inch thick.
Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned on bottom (about 10 minutes).

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream sugar and butter together; add eggs and mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Add flour and cocoa.
Flour and grease pan.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: gumbo
directions: Place in frying pan on low heat with a little oil or butter and brown lightly.

title: fruity chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken.
Place in small roaster with 2 cups water.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stan's beef tidbits
directions: Heat skillet, saute meat in salad oil unit brown.
Add peppers, onions, mushrooms, water, burgundy and all seasonings.
Cook over medium heat 15-20 minutes.
If more seasoning is needed add 1 tsp. Lawry's Season Salt.
Add cornstarch mix to thicken.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 6.

title: fancy top biscuits
directions: Separate biscuits.
Dip in or brush with melted butter.
Top with any one of the following variations.
Bake as directed on package.
Makes 10 biscuits.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix together milk, egg, sugar, salt and flour. Add yeast. Knead dough until it is smooth. Let rise until it doubles in size. Brown sausage and add cream cheese. After dough has risen, divide in half. Flatten half like a pizza. Spread egg (beaten) on the dough and then spread half of the sausage mixture. Roll it up and slice 1-inch thick. Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crab melt aways
directions: Combine and mix well with mixer the first 7 ingredients.
Fold in crabmeat.
Split English muffins and spread on crab mixture. Freeze on cookie sheet for about 45 minutes.
Put in Ziploc bags. Thaw and broil 5 minutes or until fluffy and golden brown. Quarter.

title: cheese topped green beans
directions: Wash beans; remove ends.
Cut beans in 1-inch pieces.
In medium saucepan, combine beans, water and soup mix.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until beans are tender; drain beans.
Turn into serving dish; stir in butter until melted. Combine almonds, Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Sprinkle over beans.

title: recipe for dirt
directions: Crumble Oreo cookies.
Set aside.
Cream margarine and cream cheese.
Add sugar and mix well.
Set aside.
Beat dry pudding mix and milk, slowly add Cool Whip.
Combine first mixture with pudding mixture.
If flower pot has holes in bottom, line with wax paper. Alternate layers of Oreo (first), cream mixture, Oreo on top. Chill for 2 hours.
Insert silk flowers before serving.

title: cherry cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly, spoon off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: fruit-turkey salad
directions: Core, rinse and drain lettuce.
Chill in plastic bag.
Reserve 4 whole leaves for lettuce cups; shred enough lettuce to make 4 cups.
Set aside.
Blend oil, vinegar, salt, basil, garlic powder and pepper.
Combine with turkey or chicken, onion and tomato; toss gently to mix.
Arrange lettuce cups on 4 salad plates.
Add shredded lettuce, then top with turkey mixture.
Garnish with avocado slices and tangerines or orange sections.
Serve at once. Yield: 4 servings.

title: min's sour pickles
directions: Sterilize a
gallon jar.
Wash cukes.
Mix all ingredients together and
pour over cukes.
Make sure brine is covering pickles.

title: shredded potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, sour cream, onion, 1/4 cup of butter, salt and pepper.
Add cheese.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top.
Drizzle remaining butter on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: old fashioned fruit salad
directions: Add any fresh fruit you may have in your kitchen, blueberries, kiwi, strawberries and 1 can Mandarin orange sections, drained. Combine ingredients. Toss gently and chill 1 hour. Yield: 12 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Put crescent rolls on an 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, 2/3 cup salad dressing and Hidden Valley Ranch mix.
Spread on cooled crust. Chop fine, broccoli, carrots, cauliflower, celery, green onions and green peppers.
Add shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: coconut bar cookies
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with aluminum foil.
Lightly grease. Combine butter, sugar and egg in food processor.
Whirl until creamy.
Add flour and 1 cup of walnuts.
Pulse just until combined and still in clumps.
Press in even layer with floured fingers into pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes, or until edges are golden. Cool in pan on rack.
Sprinkle chocolate chips, coconut and remaining walnuts on top.
Pour on milk.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown; cool in pan.

title: kentucky style vegetable soup
directions: Cook beef until tender.
Mix in vegetables.
Cook until tender.
Add macaroni;
cook until done.
Serve hot; best with corn bread.
Will feed 4 to 6.

title: butterscotch bran cookies
directions: Cream the butter with the brown sugar.
Add 1 egg; beat well, then stir in the bran.
Sift the flour and baking powder together; work into the creamed mixture.
Knead and shape into long rolls, about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper; store in refrigerator until firm.
Slice thinly and bake in a 400° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.	Saut onions and celery in butter, then add Cheez Whiz and cream of chicken soup. Simmer for a minute or so. Add salt and pepper. Mix rice, broccoli and cheese mixture in large bowl. Pour into large baking dish. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Makes 10 servings.

title: two minute microwave fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients 2 minutes on High.
Stir up well and add vanilla and nuts (if desired).
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate, then cut into squares.

title: wild rice and ham chowder
directions: In medium saucepan, combine 1 1/2 cups water and rice.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes or until rice is tender.
Do not drain.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
In large saucepot or Dutch oven, saute onion and garlic until tender-crisp.
Stir in flour.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in the 4 cups water and bouillon.
Add potatoes, carrots, thyme, nutmeg, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Add corn.
Cover and simmer another 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in ham, milk and rice. Remove bay leaf.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 8.

title: meat balls
directions: Shape into balls the size of a walnut, and brown in 1/4 c. hot fat.
Remove meat, and stir into fat 1/4 c. flour, 1/2 tsp. salt, 1/8 tsp. pepper.
Stir in 1 c. boiling water and 3/4 c. sour cream.
Return meat to gravy, and cook 15 minutes.
6 to 8 servings.

title: martha's banana pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Stir in milk.
Stir until smooth.
Cook until thick, then add vanilla and margarine. Line bowl with vanilla wafers.
Slice bananas on top of vanilla wafers.
Pour pudding mixture on top of this.

title: microwave german chocolate cake
directions: Pour coconut frosting in bottom of microwave-safe Bundt pan. Mix cake mix according to package directions, using oil, water and eggs.
Pour on top of frosting.
Smooth top.
Bake on High for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Turn out onto plate.
Cool and serve.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar,
salt, butter and vanilla and mix well. Add slightly
beaten
eggs.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust. Bake in
preheated
oven
at
400° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 35 minutes.
I
usually put a piece of foil over the pie for the last
few minutes so it won't get too brown on top.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook flour, butter and salt until mixed well.
Add 1/2 of the milk.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Stir often.
Add rest of milk.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Add cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Pour cheese sauce over cooked macaroni.
Bake at 400° until brown on top.

title: pesto sauce
directions: In a blender, combine basil, pepper, salt, garlic, nuts and 1 cup of oil.
Blend at high speed until ingredients are smooth, stopping the blender every 5 to 6 seconds to push herbs down with a rubber spatula.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms, pat dry, remove stems.
Chop stems and saute with sausage, garlic and parsley until sausage is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain off pan drippings.
Stir in cheese, mixing well. Spoon mixture into mushroom caps and place in a 9 X 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onion, bacon, and raisins in a bowl. Mix salad dressing, sugar and vinegar and blend well and pour over broccoli, stir well. Sprinkle cheese over top and chill. Keeps for about 3 days.

title: celery relish
directions: Grind celery, sweet peppers, onions and hot peppers; then cover with salt and boiling water.
Let stand for 10 minutes and drain.
Bring to a boil the sugar, vinegar, mustard seeds and turmeric.
Add the celery mixture and let boil for 15 minutes. Put into pint jars and seal.
Makes about 12 pints.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and place in greased casserole.
Mix crushed corn flakes and margarine.
Place on top of potato mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° (suitable for freezing).

title: dump cake
