directions: Place ingredients in order layered in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown beef with garlic; drain off fat.
Mix next 4 ingredients and stir into beef.
Stuff shells.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix everything together.
Make 12 (1-inch) meatballs.
Fry in pan until sides are brown.

title: microwave broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in microwave for 10 minutes until mixture has cheese melted well.

title: indiana-style corn dogs
directions: You will need wooden skewers.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix corn, flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg with the milk and add to corn mixture.
Stir in the melted shortening.
Drop by teaspoons in hot oil and cook 3 to 4 minutes, until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Top with powdered sugar, honey or syrup.
Yield:
about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: denver biscuits
directions: Heat milk in small saucepan to lukewarm.
Add yeast.
In large bowl, mix Crisco, sugar, milk mixture and enough flour (about 5 cups) to make consistency of cake batter.
Put in large bowl, cover and let rise.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place ribs in a large, flat pan.
Slice enough onion and lemon to lay alternately on meat.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Mix in saucepan the catsup, Worcestershire, Tabasco, chili powder, salt and water.
Bring to a boil (but don't boil); pour over meat and turn oven down to 350°.
Baste every 15 minutes for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Sauce may thicken, so add water.
Serve sauce over cooked rice.

title: pasta salad
directions: Add peas and carrots to drained pasta.
Mix oregano, onion salt, garlic salt and black pepper.
Add to pasta.
Chill 15 minutes.
Add Italian dressing and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cool cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions.
Allow to cool.
Take a fork or tines and poke cake full of holes.
Dissolve jello according to directions and pour slowly over cake evenly.
Put cake in refrigerator and chill at least 2 hours.
Frost with the Cool Whip and keep refrigerated.

title: spaghetti and bean casserole
directions: Brown ground meat.
Saute onion until tender.
Season to taste.
Add Ranch Style beans and spaghetti to meat and onion. Bake in oven at 375° until hot, then add grated cheese and bake until melted.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Add
salt and pepper to cheese and cream with margarine in mixer.
Gradually
stir
in flour and baking powder.
Drop teaspoonfuls
onto
ungreased
cookie
sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° for
15 minutes or until light brown.
Will keep in a tin for a month.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: almond roca
directions: Toast almonds in the oven (or we use the microwave) until lightly toasted.
Boil butter, sugar, corn syrup and water to 300°, stirring constantly (it takes a really long time), so the mixture doesn't stick to the bottom of the pan and burn.
When mixture reaches 300°, add chopped almonds.
Pour into greased cookie sheet. Melt chocolate over double boiler or in the microwave.
When candy has hardened, pour chocolate over all and sprinkle with some finely chopped almonds.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk.
Boil 1 minute, then add margarine. Next, add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Either drop on waxed paper or put in a 7 x 11-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan and cut into squares.
Best refrigerated.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish, covered.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until rice is tender.

title: pasta with chicken
directions: In a large skillet saute garlic for about 5 minutes.
Add chicken strips and saute until almost completely done.
Add broccoli and saute until tender; then add sun-dried tomatoes, basil, red pepper flakes, salt and pepper.
Add wine; then add the chicken broth and butter.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until heated through, stirring occasionally.
Toss the freshly cooked pasta with the chicken mixture.
Serve with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: snow rockets
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and oats. Roll into finger shapes about 1-inch long.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (or until light brown).
Roll while warm in powdered sugar.
Cool and roll again.

title: chocolate velvet
directions: Mix margarine, flour and pecans.
Spread in 2-quart Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Beat together cream cheese (room temperature), Cool Whip and powdered sugar and spread on top of first mixture.
Mix chocolate pudding with milk and beat about 2 minutes.
Spread on top of second layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Shave part of small Hershey bar on top of 4th layer.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 400°.
Prick pie crust and bake 10 minutes.
Cool.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In skillet, brown beef and onion until meat is done.
Drain fat.
Add taco seasoning mix according to package directions.

title: congealed strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Fold in thawed strawberries.
Add drained pineapple and nuts.
Place 1/2 the mixture in mold.
Spread a layer of sour cream.
Then add remaining Jell-O mixture.
Chill.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: what cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and butter which has been broken into chunks.
Stir until butter melts; set aside.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to oat mixture; mix well.
Add sugars, then eggs; mix thoroughly.
Bake in a 2-quart dish 12 minutes in microwave.
Turn dish often.
Frost with topping.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except almonds, bread crumbs and butter; put in greased casserole.
Put slivered almonds and bread crumbs on top; dot with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
(Skinned turkey parts work well, also.)
Serves 6.

title: onion pie
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Combine eggs and sour cream. Add seasonings and pour into pastry shell. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° and cook 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts. Cut in bite size pieces. Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Lay chicken in bottom.
Mix soup with sour cream. Spread over chicken. Add poppy seed to crushed crackers. Mix. Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Pour melted margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbles, 30 minutes.

title: baked italian french fries
directions: Mix together and bake in a glass dish at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: butter ball cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla; add nuts.
Mix in flour by hand. Batter will be soft.
Form into small 1-inch balls.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until just starting to brown on bottom. Roll in some powdered sugar and let cool.
Great at Christmastime!

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
This punch is good and excellent for large groups.

title: california casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed; drain well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Slice Velveeta cheese to cover the vegetables.
Roll one tube of Ritz crackers and cover the cheese.
Melt the margarine and drizzle over the top.
Bake 30 minutes in 325° oven.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and salt and pepper.
Cook egg noodles and drain.
In a baking dish, first layer cooked ground beef, green beans and tomato soup.
Add cooked egg noodles.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: green beans sorrento
directions: Cook beans.
Add all other ingredients and mix gently.

title: mac and cheese
directions: Slice your cheese.
Cook macaroni.
In a baking dish, put a layer of cooked macaroni in dish, then top with sliced cheese. Put another layer of macaroni on top of cheese, then top with more sliced cheese.
Put a little salt and pepper on it.
Pour milk in just until it will cover the first layer of cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour or until cheese is melted and brown.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir (don't beat) muffin mix.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: me~me's crab dip
directions: In medium plate, spread cream cheese in bottom of plate. Pour cocktail sauce over cream cheese and top with crabmeat. Serve cold with Captain wafers.

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Pour barbecue sauce over beef so meat is coated but no sauce sits in bottom of dish.
Place beef on bun.
Cover with remaining bun.
Place sandwiches on paper towels.
Cook in microwave, depending on your oven until meat is hot.

title: broccoli pesto cheese ravioli
directions: Blend together 1/2 the broccoli with the next 6 ingredients until smooth.
Cook ravioli according to package directions with the other half of the broccoli.
Drain.
Return to pan.
Pour blended mixture over ravioli and broccoli.
Mix well.
Top with extra Parmesan cheese.

title: cheese bacon puffs
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spread on party loaf bread.
Cook at 350° until bubbly and brown.
This is also good on large rye bread and used for a lunch.

title: no cholesterol egg noodles
directions: Mix egg whites, salt and water.
Add flour, a little at a time; mix well.
Flour bread board.
Take small amount of dough and roll out very thin.
Cut with noodle cutter or sharp knife. Bring broth to a rolling boil.
Add noodles, 2 or 3 at a time. Cover; cook very slowly for 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not uncover.

title: monkey bread
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in cooled, scalded milk.
Stir in sugar, salt, butter and flour.
Beat well.
Cover and let rise in warm place until almost double in bulk.
Punch down; roll out on a lightly floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into diamond shaped pieces, 2 1/2-inches long.
Dip in melted butter and arrange in 9-inch ring mold pan.
Pan should be about 1/2 full.
Let rise again until almost double in bulk.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven until golden brown.

title: pumpkin upside-down cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar.
Add egg mixture to pumpkin, spices and milk.
Pour mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with dry yellow cake mix.
Melt the butter or margarine and drizzle over cake.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Add chopped pecans over cake.
Return to oven and bake 30 minutes longer. Serve with Cool Whip topping.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Add all ingredients together, except onions.
Place in greased baking dish.
Top with onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: buster bars
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch glass pan; freeze.
Soften ice cream and spread over crumbs.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the peanuts.
Freeze again.
Bring to boil the sugar, evaporated milk, butter and chocolate chips; cook until thick (10 to 15 minutes).
Cool and spread over ice cream.
Top with remaining peanuts.

title: tina's "sees fudge"
directions: Place sugar and milk in heavy saucepan; boil 5 minutes.
In a large bowl, place next 6 ingredients.
Pour boiling mixture over it and stir, stir and stir.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch Pyrex. Let set at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
It's perfect every time!

title: hungarian cauliflower
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray a large baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
On a large piece of wax paper, combine flour and seasonings.
On another piece of wax paper, place cereal.
Coat florets evenly in flour mixture.
Place egg white in shallow bowl.
Dip florets in egg white, then coat in cornflake crumbs.
Place florets on prepared sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden and tender.
Serve with Ranch dressing for dipping.

title: feta cheese pita(tiropita)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add crumbled
Feta	cheese	and dry cottage cheese; blend well.
Lay a sheet
of
filo	on a board.
Brush with melted butter.
Cut
into
2-inch
wide
strips.
Place 1 teaspoon of cheese mixture on one end of pastry strip and fold corner over to make
a
triangle.
Continue
until	all cheese mixture and filo have been used.
Line triangles in a buttered shallow pan.
Bake at 350°	for
minutes
or
until golden brown.

title: stromboli sandwiches
directions: Brown together the ground beef and onion.
Pour off fat.
Add rest of ingredients to ground beef.
Slice 6 Kaiser rolls.
(Can use hamburger buns instead.)
Butter the top and bottom of each roll.
Sprinkle a little garlic powder and paprika on each roll. Add meat mixture to each bottom roll and a slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Replace roll tops and wrap in Reynold's Wrap.
Heat in 350° oven for about 15 minutes.
Recipe can be frozen, then heat about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburg noodle casserole
directions: Fry onion, pepper and meat in a small amount of oil.
Add tomato soup and noodles.
Put in a casserole, sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: homemade hot apple cider
directions: Combine the sugar, spices, lemon slices and water in a saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Strain the liquid into a large pot.
Discard the lemon and spices.
Add cider and juices.
Heat through and serve.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix egg yolks and sugar.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in milk.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and 1/2 cup coconut.
Cool slightly.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar together and boil for 2 minutes.
Mix cold water and lemon gelatin; add to pineapple mixture.
Crumble cream cheese.
Keep bowl and beaters in refrigerator before using. Beat milk until stiff.
Add crumbled cream cheese and whipped cream to the pineapple mixture.
Mix well and chill.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together with electric beater.
Pour in baked 8-inch pie shell.
Let set in the refrigerator 3 to 4 hours. Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: family biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients. (I use my hands.)
Knead on a floured board, roll out and cut with a biscuit cutter or a glass.
Bake at 425°.

title: koolaid punch
directions: Mix sugar and 4 cups water and heat until sugar dissolves. Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: honey sauce
directions: Put butter, honey, water and salt in saucepan; blend cornstarch with 1/4 cup of this mixture.
Return to saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickens and comes to boil.
Boil 2 or 3 minutes; remove from heat and cool. Nice for baked apples, puddings, pound cake, etc.

title: millie's good stuff
directions: Steam the zucchini and set it aside.
In a skillet, saute the grated carrots and the onion briefly; set aside.
Combine the sour cream and the cream of chicken soup and gently add to the carrot and onion mixture.
Gently stir in the dry dressing mix.
Add the zucchini last and toss/stir gently.
Bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes.
Check this at 30 minutes and if it's getting too brown, cover it loosely with foil for the last 10-15 minutes.

title: cranberry-grape salad
directions: Grind cranberries and cover with sugar.
Let this stand while you prepare the other ingredients.
Add the grapes, celery, nut meats and marshmallows to the cranberries.
Chill for several hours.
Add Cool Whip.
Serves 12.
This can be used as a salad or is sweet enough for a dessert.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Bake pie shell.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in medium saucepan. Gradually stir in water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Gradually stir part of the hot mixture into the egg yolks. Blend into hot mixture in pan.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter, lemon peel, lemon juice and food coloring.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange layers of onions, soup and nuts in a large casserole dish.
Top with cornflake crumbs.
Melt margarine and pour on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a buttered 11x7 casserole dish.

title: aunt mary's punch
directions: Mix together and chill. Makes a little over a gallon.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Heat margarine or butter until bubbly.
Separate egg yolks from egg whites.
Put egg yolks, lemon juice, salt and cayenne in blender.
Cover; turn blender on high speed.
Immediately remove cover.
Add hot butter or margarine in slow, steady stream.
To keep, store in refrigerator.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: seafood steam pot
directions: Various seafood can be used such as crab legs, oysters in shell, clams, etc.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix into loaf.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain, rinse and cool.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and cover tightly.
Best to make a day or 2 before serving.
Mix occasionally.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: candy bar cookies(pillsbury bakeoff)
directions: Cream oleo and gradually add sifted powdered sugar.
Cream well and add vanilla, Pet milk and salt.
Blend in flour.
Chill for easier handling.
Roll out half dough at a time to 12 x 8-inch size on floured board.
Cut into 3 x 1 1/2-inch rectangles or 2-inch squares (or with cookie cutter).
Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 325° until lightly browned (12 to 16 minutes); cool. Spread 1 teaspoon filling on each.
Top with 1/2 teaspoon chocolate icing.
Decorate with 1/2 pecan.

title: dad's favorite fudge pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together the flour, salt, sugar, baking powder and 1 1/2 tablespoons cocoa.
Combine vanilla, milk and butter and stir into dry ingredients.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine white and brown sugars with 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Mix with hot water, stirring to dissolve.
Pour over the batter in the pan.
Bake 45 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream, if desired.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Mix butter, sugar and cream in a saucepan and simmer for 5 minutes. Beat 1/2 minute. Serve hot or cold.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Add to a pan with 1 1/2 sticks melted butter.
Bake at 375° until golden brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan. Stir until well heated; do not boil. Makes approximately 6 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: karen's chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and garlic.
Add chili powder and flour; coat well.
Add all other ingredients, except beans, and cook slowly (covered) for two hours.
Add beans and cook 30 more minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and drain.
Mix Cheez Whiz and soup together; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: aunt bill's microwave candy
directions: Combine sugar, buttermilk, soda and butter.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Punch holes in wrap and microwave 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Stir and turn dish.
Continue cooking for 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Return to oven to 2 minutes or longer (until soft ball forms in cold water).
Add vanilla and beat with electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Add pecans and beat until thick enough to spread in a buttered 12 x 7-inch dish.
Cool and cut in pieces.

title: 7-up mistletoe punch
directions: Place berries in blender and blend until smooth.
Place in punch bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serves 36.

title: fry chick casserole
directions: Cook, drain and rinse noodles thoroughly.
Mix all ingredients together.
(Save sprinkled of cheese for the top of the casserole.)
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° until casserole bubbles.
Serve hot.

title: spam and cheese bake
directions: Combine and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole; top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: maple bacon cheddar cake(servings:  8 to 12)
directions: Cut bacon strips crosswise in 1/2-inch pieces, then fry until golden; drain and keep warm.
Combine remaining ingredients except for cheese.
Mix until smooth, then stir in 1 cup of cheese.
Set aside the other cup of cheese.
Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes until very lightly brown and springs back when lightly touched.
After removing from oven, brush the top with melted butter, then sprinkle reserved cheese and bacon pieces on top. Serve with additional maple syrup and fresh fruit garnish.
Serves 8 to 12 portions.
This is an easy breakfast menu for weekend guests!

title: cantaloupe jam
directions: Combine cantaloupe, peaches and sugar and let juice form. Then add pineapple.
Boil 20 minutes.
Add lemon Jell-o.
Boil 2 more minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine egg, milk, 2/3 cup cracker crumbs, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Stir in corn and onions, mix well.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole.
Toss butter with remaining crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of corn mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix everything together.
Bake in greased and floured 1-pound bread tin at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: barbecue(recipe will serve 50 people)
directions: Simmer for 1/2 hour.
This may be thickened with cornstarch if more is desired.
Serve on buns.
Very good warmed up also.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Put 1 tablespoon of oil in bottom of large pot.
Add garlic and chicken and brown.
Add tea ball, allspice and bay leaves. Cook on medium heat with lid on for 10 minutes.
Stir frequently. Add vinegar and soy sauce.
Boil with lid off for 5 minutes. Cover with lid and turn heat down to a simmer.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Uncover and cook until liquid is reduced somewhat, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika and sugar; stir and serve over steamed rice.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in 2 tablespoons fat. Add water.
Cover and simmer until tender. Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Add syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and salt. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour over hot cooked pork.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add pineapple, green pepper and onion.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes.
Serve over chow mein noodles or rice.

title: "loukoumathes" - honey puffs
directions: Pour warm water into large mixing bowl.
Crumble cake of yeast in water until dissolved; add salt.
Stir in flour gradually and beat with a wooden spoon until smooth.
Cover bowl with a large plate and a clean dish towel.
Set aside in warm place to rise. Requires about 1/2 hour to 45 minutes to rise.

title: six bean minestrone
directions: In large saucepot place all dried beans and 12 cups water; let stand overnight.
Bring beans and water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours until tender.
In skillet, cook 1/2 cup bean liquid, onion, garlic, celery and parsley 5 minutes; add to cooked beans with tomatoes, potatoes, carrots, peas and green beans.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes.
Add zucchini, cabbage and enough water to make 7 quarts of soup.
Cook until zucchini is tender.

title: spicy poultry stuffing
directions: Saute onion, garlic and celery in vegetable oil until clear. Mix bread crumbs.
To the crumbs add finely chopped green pepper and parsley.
Then add cooked giblets, beaten eggs and soup to mixture.
Add sauteed vegetables.
Mix thoroughly.
Add fowl stock for a soft consistency.
Fil the fowl cavity with stuffing.
Do not stuff tightly.
The remaining stuffing should be placed in a greased baking dish.
Cover.
Cook for 35 minutes in a 450° oven. Serve with your favorite roasted fowl.
You may also stuff pork chops.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook chicken breast until tender.
Cut into small pieces and put on bottom of casserole.
Cook broccoli, drain well and put on top of chicken.
Then add mushroom and celery soups.
Then add instant rice and put in milk.
Lastly, put Cheez Whiz on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: jeanne's peach pie
directions: Line pie shell with peaches.
Mix sugar, flour and half and half; bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour over peaches and bake at 400° for about 60 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: judy's new mexican breakfast
directions: Brown the sausage; drain it and set it aside to cool. In a bowl, beat the eggs. Add the milk, cheese, salt and mustard. Fold in the bread, the chilies and the cooled sausage. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 casserole and cover with aluminum foil. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate-prune cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until blended.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla, chocolate chips and prunes.
Spoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned. Gently remove from cookie sheets and let cool on wire racks.

title: cocoa bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except nuts.
Beat with spoon 30 seconds. Stir in nuts.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake 60 to 70 minutes. Insert wooden pick in center.
If clean when removed, bread is done. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan. Wrap tightly in foil. Cool completely.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: mexican hot sauce
directions: You will need a blender and a frying pan or skillet.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Barbecue sauce will keep up to 1 week in refrigerator.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese, whip and combine with next 4 ingredients. Beat until light and fluffy.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven, allow to cool for 5 minutes.
Blend sour cream, with 3 1/2 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Pour over pie and bake for additional 10 minutes.
Refrigerate 5 hours before serving.
Serves 10 to 12. Very yummy and very rich!

title: strong thang
directions: Pour tiny amounts into glass.
More enjoyable if at a party or if your meal starts to get dull.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, sifted with salt and soda.
Add sour cream and flavoring alternately.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in greased and floured pan.
Let cool.

title: grandma's sweet & sour poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil and poppy seed in blender or food processor. Slowly add oil while running blender.
Add poppy seed and run again just to mix.

title: pork cutlets
directions: Rinse pork loin and trim off excess fat.
Slice into 1/4 inch slices.
Mix flour, salt, pepper, and garlic.
Mix eggs and buttermilk with whisk.
Dip each slice in egg mixture then into flour mixture.
Fry in 1/4 inch of oil in a deep skillet until golden brown.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine tapioca, sugar, rhubarb, salt and orange rind and let stand while making pie crust.
After crust is rolled and in pie plate, fill with rhubarb filling and dot with butter, about 1 1/2 tablespoons.
Cover with top crust and bake in hot oven at 425° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 45 minutes.
(Pie usually bubbles over in oven so it is wise to have aluminum foil or a pie catcher under your shelf in oven.)

title: crunchy pea salad(serves four)
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Stir in dressing.
Serve each portion on one lettuce leaf.

title: 7-up cake
directions: To cake mix, add eggs, vanilla pudding mix and oil.
Beat well.
Add 7-Up slowly.
Pour into three 8-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until cake tests done.

title: pizza lovers soup
directions: Combine ingredients, except bread and cheese.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Toast bread rounds.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Chill for several hours.

title: baked apple 'n sausage pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Generously butter 10-inch round baking dish.
Combine pancake mix, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg in bowl.
Add eggs, milk and butter.
Mix well.
Stir in apple.
Pour into baking dish.
Arrange sausage on batter.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut in wedges and serve with syrup.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their jackets.

Peel and slice thinly. Slowly fry bacon in skillet. Drain on paper. Saute onion in bacon fat until golden brown. Blend the flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and dash of pepper in with the onion over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat.

Stir in water and vinegar and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute. Stir in carefully the potatoes and crumbled bits of bacon. Remove from heat, cover and let stand until ready to serve.
Serve with breaded pork loin (thin slices).

title: slaw
directions: Chop cabbage.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Pour over vegetables; let set overnight.
Will last for days.

title: lemon oat bars(a 1957 recipe; out again in 1985)
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together condensed milk and lemon juice until blended; stir in lemon rind.
Reserve.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Cut the unpeeled oranges into chunks.
Grind the cranberries and oranges together in a food mill.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours prior to serving.

title: zucchini casserole with chilies
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain and cool.

title: potato fans
directions: Scrub whole potatoes.
Make slices, 1/8-inch wide, in potato, but do not slice through.
(This may be done by placing potato in a large spoon and slicing down.)
Place potatoes, cut side up, in baking dish.
Drizzle half of shortening over potatoes.
Sprinkle crumbs over potatoes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Drizzle remaining shortening over potatoes.
Bake 15 minutes longer, or until brown.

title: cookies instead
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Mix cake mix with the eggs and oil. Batter will be thick.
Spoon onto cookie sheet. Will spread when baking. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Ovens vary so check for doneness.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet, then remove to wire cooling rack.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jacket until done.
Cool and dice.
Mix well with remaining ingredients.
Duke's mayonnaise is preferred, but any mayonnaise may be used.

title: english toffee dessert
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add candy and stir well.
Cool (sauce thickens as it cools).
Place strawberries in serving dishes.
Dollop each with 2 tablespoons of sour cream.
Top with 2 to 3 teaspoons of sauce.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix together and bake in 350° oven until light brown.
Cool.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except corn flakes, until blended.
Stir in corn flakes.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet; bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: steamed cake
directions: Mix Bisquick and sugar.
Beat egg lightly before adding to dry ingredients.
Add
milk.
Do not overbeat.	Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan; steam for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: orange zucchini squares
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Stir in nuts, if desired, and zucchini.
In another bowl, beat egg whites lightly. Add orange juice concentrate and oil.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Add orange peel. Spoon into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes.
Can be frosted or sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: overnight cauliflower salad
directions: Layer first 3 ingredients in order given in large bowl. Combine sour cream and mayonnaise; mix well and spread evenly over the top of vegetables, sealing to edge of bowl.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients in order given.
Cover bowl tightly with plastic wrap and chill overnight.

title: horseradish dip
directions: Melt cheese, then stir in Miracle Whip and horseradish. Cool in fridge for 1 hour. Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Brown bacon in skillet.
Remove bacon and saute onion in bacon grease.
Add next 3 items and simmer about 5 minutes.
Drain green beans and put in casserole.
Crumble bacon into the sauce and pour over beans.
Do not stir.
Bake about 40 minutes until heated. Lightly stir and serve.

title: good easy punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Divide into two gallon jars.
Add lemonade and juice to each jar with water;
stir well.
Chill before serving.

title: beef stew
directions: Do not brown meat.
Pour all ingredients (except carrots and potatoes) into a 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Add the vegetables the last 30 minutes.
This may also be made on the top of the stove.
It will not require this amount of time when done on top of the stove.

title: applesauce spice muffins
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs.
Mix spices with flour. Add soda to applesauce and heat.
Add flour mixture and applesauce mixture to butter. Add vanilla. Grease small muffin pans.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while warm.
These are even better the next day.
(They also freeze well.)
Yields 8 dozen. Very good!

title: kay's baked beans
directions: Cut bacon into bite-size pieces and fry.
Place the beans with juice into a large, covered bean pot or roasting pan.
Add the listed ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake, covered, stirring occasionally.

title: pear pie
directions: Fill unbaked crust with pared and cored pear halves, cut side down and wheel designed.
Mix the remaining ingredients well and pour over pears.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cream pudding
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and pineapple juice.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour a few tablespoons of the hot liquid over beaten eggs and stir well.
Return to stove and cook another 5 minutes over very low heat, stirring constantly. Stir in margarine, lemon juice and crushed pineapple.
Cool and serve with a dollop of whipped topping.

title: rice soup
directions: Mix water and rice.
Dice celery; add to rice.
Fry meat, onion and pepper.
Cook until done.
Add pureed tomatoes to mixture.
Add mushrooms; simmer all together.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix together ingredients and spread on party rye.
Put under broiler until bubbly.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine; set aside. Mix whipped topping with milk and whip until stiff. Add sugar and cream cheese.
Layer crumbs in dish, then add 2 cans pie filling. Top with whipped topping mixture.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix together flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, cinnamon and melted butter.
Place 1/2 of mixture in a 7 x 10-inch pan.
Cover with rhubarb.

title: old fashioned meat loaf
directions: Mix all together in a bowl, then put in pan.
Cook at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: mincemeat drop cookies
directions: Cream the shortening.
Add sugar, egg, mincemeat, flour and baking powder sifted together.
Add to shortening and mix.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet (greased).
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Yields approximately 2 dozen.

title: easy green bean casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Add soup.
Drain green beans; add to beef mixture. Cook for 5 minutes.
Put in casserole dish.
Place mashed potatoes on top.
Cook in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles and set aside.
Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Add seasoning mix, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Stir well and cook about 10 minutes.
Put a layer of meat mixture in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle Mozzarella on top of that and then add a layer of noodles and another layer of meat mixture and remaining cheese on top of that.
Sprinkle generously with oregano.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water in a Dutch oven; stir in orange juice and next 3 ingredients.
Pour mixture into a large plastic container, then freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 1 hour before serving.
Place in a punch bowl and break into chunks. Add lemon-lime beverage; stir until slushy.
Yields about 6 quarts.

title: taco delight
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a large skillet; add salsa, tomato sauce and bouillon cube.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Serve with remaining ingredients.

title: egg butter
directions: Bring syrup to boil.
Using whisk, slowly and vigorously stir in eggs.
Remove from heat.
Serve over hot, buttered biscuits.

title: easy cheese coffee cake
directions: Spray bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam cooking spray.
Layer pan with 1 can of the crescent rolls.

title: chicken crescents
directions: In a nonstick skillet, saute celery and onion in butter for 3 to 4 minutes or until tender. Add chicken and soup; mix well. Remove from the heat.

title: outstanding meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread apple slices evenly in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch glass pan.
Crumble remaining ingredients together in mixing bowl. Sprinkle crumbled topping mixture on top of apples in pan. Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: mars krispies
directions: Melt margarine and Mars bars or Snickers until creamy.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Pat into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut into small squares and serve.
Great for snacks.

title: cherry sauce with brandy
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a 1-quart glass bowl. Gradually add brandy, stirring to make a smooth paste.
Add lemon juice and cherries.
Stir to blend well.
Cover bowl and microwave at High for 10 to 13 minutes or until sauce is hot and thickened, stirring twice.
Serve over ice cream or cake.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all together.
Add dash of salt and chill.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Remove casing from sausage; crumble sausage meat and fry with garlic.
Add cooked and drained broccoli.
Add salt, pepper and parsley to taste.
Drain well.
Divide mixture into half.
Roll out dough (like a small pizza).
Spread 1/2 mixture on dough.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Roll each dough up to look like an Italian loaf of bread.
Place on a flat cookie sheet (ungreased) with seam side down.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 2 loaves.
Cool slightly, cut and serve, or freeze for a later time.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine dry ingredients. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 32 to 34 cookies.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Stir cabbage, onion and pepper together
with sugar sprinkled in.
Bring other ingredients to a boil and pour hot mixture over cabbage.
Do not stir. Cover and refrigerate over night.
Stir before serving.

title: jim's french fries
directions: Vigorously scrub the potatoes; do not peel.
Arrange them loosely on a cookie sheet and place in a 400° oven for 30 minutes (or place them on a microwave-safe plate and nuke on High for 12 minutes).
Spray lightly with Pam and place under broiler until brown (3 to 5 minutes).

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter and set aside.
Mix sugar, flour and baking powder together.
Add milk and cherries; mix.
Add butter and mix.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: connie's zucchini casserole
directions: Bring to a boil the zucchini and onion.
Simmer 5 minutes; drain.
Add grated carrots. Melt margarine.
In a separate container, mix stuffing mix and seasoning into melted margarine and add all but 2/3 cup to zucchini mixture. Add chicken soup and sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over top.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Enjoy!

title: praline pie(makes 6 servings)
directions: Brush pie crust with egg white.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes; set aside.

title: san juan taco salad
directions: Cook meat in large skillet over medium-high heat until browned.
Drain off pan drippings.
Add 2 tablespoons of the picante sauce, oregano and salt.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly; let cool.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Crumble corned beef into a medium bowl. Add cottage cheese, scallions, green pepper, parsley and seasonings. Mix thoroughly. Chill several hours to blend flavors and to firm mixture. Remove mixture from bowl and shape into a ball. Spread cream cheese evenly over ball. Sprinkle paprika and parsley in a sizable sheet of plastic wrap (optional). Wrap ball in this plastic and refrigerate. Serve on a cheese board or tray with assorted crackers and thick cucumber slices for spreading. Garnish with sprigs of parsley, if desired.

title: german skillet beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; crumble and set aside.
Cook onions in bacon drippings until tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until heated through, stirring often.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield: 4 (1/2 cup each) servings.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and 1/2 Cool Whip (set aside the other half).
Mix well and pour in a 9-inch pie crust.
Put rest of Cool Whip on top and refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
Low-fat and sugar free.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Chill. You can make an ice ring (using additional Hawaiian Punch) to float in punch bowl to keep punch cool while serving.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: In a medium bowl, cream together 1/2 cup of the sugar, the shortening and the egg; sift together flour, baking powder, salt and the nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon on a medium size plate. Remove puffs from oven and immediately dip each into melted butter, then into cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Coat all over.
Serve warm.

title: pastel pound cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add eggs 1 at a time, beating after each addition. Add extracts. Combine the flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition. Pour half the batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Sprinkle with marshmallows. Top with remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan. Cool completely. Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: dream cream
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into 1 1/2 to 2 gallon freezer can.
Add enough milk to fill can about 3/4 full.
Freeze right away and serve at once.
Great ice cream.

title: fred's salad
directions: Layer in a long, shallow dish.
Crumble bacon on top and cover with mayonnaise.
Very good!
The longer it chills, the better the flavor.

title: mexican hamburger meat
directions: Heat soup, milk, cheese and tomatoes on low heat until warm. Brown hamburg and onion; drain off grease.

title: twinkies strawberry banana dessert
directions: Cut Twinkies in half; line pan (long oblong).
Make a layer of strawberries, layer of bananas and a layer of vanilla pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Clean and steam each vegetable in 1 inch of water for time given for each vegetable.
Drain very well!!!
Layer 1/2 broccoli, 1/2 cauliflower, 1/2 carrots, 1/2 mushrooms, 1/2 cheese and repeat.
Blot cream of mushroom soup on top of last layer.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let set 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Let rhubarb and sugar stand overnight.
Next morning, boil, stirring constantly, about 10 minutes or until tender.
Add jello powder and pineapple.
Bring to a boil, skim off foam with metal spoon and pour into clean glasses.
Cover at once with hot paraffin.

title: marilyn's hamburger quiche
directions: Beat the eggs.
Combine with milk, mayo and cornstarch.
Add hamburger and cheese.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
May add green pepper, onion or whatever else sounds good.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into a ball and roll in nuts.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
When golden brown, add the peas, taco sauce and water.
Cook until done.
Serve over warm rice.

title: tortilla chip dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of pie dish, then spread chili on top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle approximately 1/3 cup cheese on top.
Microwave for 2 to 4 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with chips.
It's a family favorite!

title: zucchini-beef casserole
directions: Allow heavy skillet to become very hot over high heat and brown beef, stirring constantly.
Lower heat to medium. Add tomato sauce, salt, Tabasco, sugar and Worcestershire sauce and cook about 5 minutes until well blended.
Add green onions.
Remove from heat.
Slice zucchini in 1/4-inch rounds.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Blend with pastry blender or fork the butter, flour, cheese and pepper. Fold in Rice Krispies. Roll in 2 inch balls; place on cookie sheet and flatten with fork. Bake in 350° oven 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix the butter or margarine, sugars and egg.
Sift and stir in flour, baking soda and salt making a stiff dough.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown with soft-center.

title: turkey crunch(second day turkey casserole)
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Stir soup into mayonnaise; toss with turkey mixture.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with noodles.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until mixture is bubbling.
Serves 6.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef in a skillet with olive oil and garlic.
After browning, add tomato sauce, salt, oregano and pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package in salted water for about 15 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
Fill a casserole dish with alternate layers of noodles, sauce and cheese, ending with a layer of sauce and topping with Mozzarella cheese and some Parmesan cheese.
Bake in oven at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until bubbly.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: miracle cookies
directions: In large pan, bring sugar, margarine and milk to full boil. Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Drop by large teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cool and serve.

title: succotash
directions: Cook limas as directed on package.
Drain some broth from corn.
Mix all together and simmer a short time.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Start with well-beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Pour mixture into an unbaked 9-inch deep-dish pie crust.
Bake 45 minutes to an hour, or until pie "sets" and is a light golden brown.
Cool before serving.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: In a jar with a tight fitting lid, combine garlic, mustard, honey, vinegar, lemon juice and oil.
Cover and shake well to combine.
If desired, add herbs and mix well.
Refrigerate. Wonderful for pasta and vegetables and tossed salads.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Combine orange juice, rind and egg in different bowl.
Pour liquids in dry ingredients, mixing just enough until moist.
Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar after cocoa has been mixed with part of sugar.
Add whole egg yolks.
Add alternately flour, milk and vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
This makes 4 layers.
Knock pans of batter on table to jar out bubbles before putting in oven. Bake in 350° oven 20 minutes.
This cake better several days after cooking.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onions.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Zucchini may also be used in place of yellow squash.

title: french apple pie
directions: Toss together the apples, cinnamon and sugar.
Place the apple mixture in the pie crust.
Cream together the butter and brown sugar.
Use a pastry blender or 2 knives to combine the flour with the creamed mixture until the mixture becomes crumbly.
Top the pie with this crumbly mixture.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes (until bubbly and lightly browned).

title: southwestern dip
directions: Beat together the 1st three ingredients. Fold in grated cheese. Hollow out loaf and cut up into 1 inch cubes of bread. Put in cheese mixture into loaf. Bake 45 minutes at 300° with foil over it on a cookie sheet. Toast 1 inch bread cubes for dipping in the cheese mixture.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Heat
soup and gelatin together. Remove from
heat
and mix other ingredients together with soup mixture.
Serve
with corn chips.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: In large bowl, whisk mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt & pepper. Add chicken, onion, celery, apple or grapes, walnuts and raisins. Toss. Makes 4 servings.

title: maree spencer's chocolate cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs and beat until smooth. Stir in cocoa.
Add flour with soda and salt. Alternate with milk. Add vanilla and chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350°.

title: smoky ribs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; set aside.

Cut ribs into serving size pieces; place in a large Dutch oven. Cover ribs with water. Add garlic salt and pepper. Bring water to a boil; cover and reduce heat. Cook over slow coals 45 minutes or to desired doneness, turning frequently. Brush ribs with sauce during last 15 minutes. Heat remaining sauce and serve with ribs. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: ruth's soup
directions: Simmer onion in water and consomme until tender.
Add other ingredients.
Bring to boil; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pinto bean cake
directions: Cook and mash pinto beans, then measure.
Bake all in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Put the tuna in the bottom, then add the celery, soup-milk mixture, chives and soy sauce, ending with the nuts and noodles on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: fruit cocktail jello salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Make 2 cups juice plus 2 cups cold water.
Heat juice.
Add Jell-O and mashed cream cheese.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour over fruit; add salt and chill.
Cut in squares or put in molds.
Place half a cherry on top of each serving.

title: strawberry cream squares
directions: Dissolve strawberry gelatin in hot water. Add frozen strawberries. Let stand until strawberries soften. Add pineapple (with juice). Add pecans; mix well. Pour half of mixture into Pyrex dish. Chill until firm. Spoon sour cream over firm gelatin; spread evenly. Pour remaining gelatin mixture over sour cream. Chill until firm. Cut into squares before serving.

title: fried fish
directions: Dip fish in buttermilk.
Coat with flour and salt.
Deep fry in hot oil about 400° for 4 minutes or until brown.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in two pie shells. Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: apple slices
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir well.
Place half the dough in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan and spread as thin as you can.
Cover with a layer or two of sliced apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Put dots of dough over the apples.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine cheese soup, sour cream, onion, margarine, salt and pepper.
Mix well; fold in hash browns and pour into baking dish.
Toss cornflakes with margarine and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until golden and potatoes are tender.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil until foamy.
Combine flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch dish, melt butter.
Pour frozen hash browns over butter.
Cover with mixture of the soup and sour cream. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour.

title: shredded beef
directions: Place chuck roast in big roasting pan with all the ingredients. Place the onion slices on top and around the chuck roast.
Cook at 250° overnight (11 P.M. until 6 or 7 A.M.).
Cool; take out of pan and pull the beef apart (shred it).
When ready to serve place in crock-pot, heat and serve with rolls.

title: aunt bill's microwave candy
directions: Use a microwave container which holds at least three times the amount of ingredients, or it will boil over.
Combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and butter.
Cover with plastic wrap; punch holes in wrap to allow steam to escape.
Microwave on Roast (70% of power) for 15 minutes.
Stir; continue cooking on Roast for 13 to 15 minutes, until soft ball forms in cold water or 236° on candy thermometer.
Do not put thermometer in microwave.
Add vanilla; beat with electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Watch closely! Add nuts and pour into a buttered 8 x 8-inch dish.
Cool; cut into pieces.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Wash, quarter and cook potatoes in jacket.
Drain, cool and peel.
Shred coarsely with grater.
In bowl, combine potato shreds with sour cream, onions and 2/3 of Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper. Mix well and transfer to shallow baking dish (9 or 10-inches). Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Dust with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: marjorie preston's crabmeat casserole
directions: Make cream sauce with the butter, flour and milk in the top of a double boiler.
Add onion, grated cheese, egg, salt, pepper and crabmeat (broken up).
Put in casserole and cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° until sauce bubbles through, about 20 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli chowder
directions: Combine the broth, onion and broccoli in a saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce the heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add the potato flakes; blend thoroughly.
Stir in the chicken, cheese and milk.
Cook over low heat until the mixture is hot and the cheese is melted.

title: peanut meringue pie
directions: Combine in saucepan 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and flour. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks and cook 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat and add peanuts and vanilla. Pour into pastry shell.
Make meringue with egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes or until meringue is lightly browned.

title: mashed potato salad
directions: Take a large bowl and put potatoes in.
Toss in plenty of mayonnaise or salad dressing, chopped pickles and lemon juice, then add a little catsup, some mustard, onion and a little pickle juice.
Mix up the mess and serve.
You'll never forget it.

title: fudge
directions: Mix until blended powdered sugar and cocoa.
Add butter and condensed milk and microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and mix on high speed with hand mixer until gloss fades.
Put into 9 x 9-inch buttered pan.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into a Pam sprayed casserole dish. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: haystacks
directions: In top of double boiler, melt butterscotch chips. Add peanut butter.
Remove from heat and mix in potatoes.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: low-fat oven-fried chicken
directions: Line baking pan with foil and rub a little margarine on bottom.
Mix flour, cumin powder, pepper and paprika together. Mix egg and milk together.
Roll chicken pieces in egg mixture, then roll in flour mixture.
Place in baking pan.
Dot with margarine.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 400° to 450°.

title: vegetable strata
directions: Whisk together eggs, egg whites, milk, basil and pepper.
Dip bread slices in egg mixture and arrange, overlapping, in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add vegetables to remaining egg mixture with cheese and onion.
Mix well; pour over bread. Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.
Ten minutes before finished baking, spoon on tomato sauce.
Serves 8.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: In a skillet, fry bacon until lightly browned.
Stir in onion, carrots, celery and potato.
Cook until tender, stirring constantly.
Add clams, tomatoes, parsley, flavor enhancer, salt and thyme.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Spray Bundt pan and layer all ingredients into pan in the order they are listed.
Cover with sprayed wax paper and let set on cupboard overnight.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Take out of oven and turn immediately onto glass plate.

title: baked bean pot
directions: Drain juice off beans, except pork and beans.
Mix into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butter cream frosting
directions: Mix butter and shortening, add vanilla.
Start mixing sugar in, one cup at a time.
Mix in milk.
If you want chocolate frosting all you have to add is 1/2 c. cocoa.
Spread on cake.

title: chocolate mint layer squares
directions: Melt unsweetened chocolate and 1/2 cup butter in top of a double boiler over simmering water. Cool.
Combine eggs and 1 cup sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, walnuts and cooled chocolate. Spread into a 9-inch square baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix cooking oil and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add all sifted dry ingredients.
Batter will be very stiff.
Add diced apples and chopped nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 1/2 x 13 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May be served with ice cream or whipped cream topping.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook sausage until brown.
Drain fat. Separate rolls and press into a 12-inch pizza pan (points to center).
Scoop sausage, potatoes and cheese on top.
In bowl, blend eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour onto crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: orange cream shake
directions: Pour all ingredients into a blender and blend; pour into a glass.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Combine flour and margarine, mix with pastry blender.
Add pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, don't brown.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip, reserving some Cool Whip for topping.
Spread over cool crust. Combine milk and pudding.
Pour over cheese layer.
Add thick layer of Cool Whip over top of pudding.
Let set.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, drain.
Cook spaghetti and drain. In a 9 x 12-inch pan mix all other ingredients.
Add spaghetti and ground beef mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: In a large bowl, gradually stir whipped topping into marshmallow cream.
Stir in mint extract and food coloring; fold in mints.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, at least 4 hours or overnight.
Frozen mixture will be firm, but not hard.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: alison's spinach salad
directions: You will need a large bowl, jar with lid (or Good Seasons cruet).

title: molasses pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: pink coconut cake
directions: Place coconut and 1 tablespoon Jell-O in jar.
Shake until coconut is evenly tinted.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Mix the first four ingredients with one package of the shredded chipped beef.
Refrigerate until able to form in a mold.
Roll in other package of shredded chipped beef.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water and let cool.
Whip cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Add all to cooled Jell-O.
Makes 6 to 8 individual molds.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Cream the shortening, sugar, salt and eggs.
Add lukewarm scalded milk and potatoes to yeast.
Stir these ingredients together.
Add sifted flour to make a stiff dough and knead.
Place in a large bowl which has been greased with oil. Turn to grease top also.
Let rise to double in bulk in warm place. Knead again slightly.
Place in bowl and refrigerate.
One hour before baking, make into rolls and let rise.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: picante sauce
directions: Coarsely grind tomatoes, peppers and onion in food processor. Place all ingredients except cumin and oregano in large heavy pot. Simmer uncovered over low heat to desired consistency.
Remove from heat and add cumin and oregano.
Put in jars and seal.
Hot water bath for 3 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 pints.

title: marinated sliced tomato salad
directions: Peel and slice 4 large tomatoes.
Arrange in a shallow dish. Combine salad oil, lemon juice, minced garlic salt and oregano. Pour over tomatoes.
Chill covered for 1 hour.
Must do ahead of time.
Serves 6.

title: angel food "dream cake"
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 4 tablespoons of cold water; add boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
Combine sugar, pineapple, salt and lemon juice.
Add to cooled gelatin mixture.
Let partially congeal.
Fold in 1 tub Cool Whip.

title: cranberry-sauced turkey steaks
directions: In a bowl, stir together margarine and soy sauce.
Rinse turkey; pat dry.
Place turkey on unheated rack of broiler pan. Brush on margarine soy mixture.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Turn and brush again with soy mixture.
Broil for 4 to 6 minutes more, until turkey is tender and no longer pink.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Spread 1 pkg. crescent rolls on the bottom of ungreased 9 x 13 pan.
Mix softened cream cheese, egg yolk, sugar and vanilla well.
Spread cheese mixture on top and place second pkg. of crescent rolls on top of this.
Sprinkle topping on.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, lower oven to 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: oven tostada
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain well.
Add taco seasoning, water and refried beans.
Press crescent rolls into 7 1/2 x 11 3/4-inch greased casserole dish, forming a crust.
Layer crushed corn chips over crust.
Pour ground beef mixture on top.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares; serve with condiments of your choice on top.
Serves 8.

title: peach jello mold
directions: In a blender put peaches with juice.
Cube cream cheese. Blend with peaches until smooth.
Dissolve peach jello in boiling water.
Stir.
Add stirred jello to blender with cheese and peaches.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into favorite dish or mold. Refrigerate.

title: stripped delight cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs 1/4 cup sugar and melted margarine.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 15 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Adjust amounts of macaroni, sauce and cheese to suit any size family.
Cook macaroni and drain.
In a glass baking dish, layer macaroni, pizza toppings, Pizza Quick sauce and cheese.
Continue layers and top with a lot of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 425° about 15 to 20 minutes to heat through.
Serve hot.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef into small bite size pieces (sprinkle with unseasoned tenderizer or Cavender's Greek seasoning, if you wish).
Slowly heat large, heavy skillet.	Melt margarine (3 tablespoons); add beef.
Over high heat, sear quickly on all sides.
Remove beef as it browns and put aside.

title: orange salad
directions: Cook first four ingredients, over medium heat, until thick. Set aside to cool.
Mix in oranges and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate two hours before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Roll chicken in flour.
Brown in small amount of shortening. Drain off excess.
Put in baking dish.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over chicken.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave cook cheese
directions: Put in large bowl the cottage cheese and baking soda.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Then microwave on High 5 minutes.
Melt oleo and Velveeta cheese and add to mixture.
Mix cornstarch and milk together.
Add to other ingredients and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Pour into 1/2-pint jar or small jelly jars.

title: tabatha's dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese. Blend in picante sauce. Spread on serving plate. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Top with lettuce, onion, tomatoes and shredded cheese. Serve with chips.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix together, but leave lumpy.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Drizzle butter on top.

title: clam appetizer
directions: Saute margarine, clams (save juice), onion and garlic.
Add spices while stirring.
When about done, add lemon juice and bread crumbs.
Add clam juice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Clam Appetizer is done when golden brown.

title: short paste(pie crust or pot pie top)
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder; rub in lightly with the fingers the lard.
Mix into
a firm dough with the ice water and roll out once on a floured board.
Handle as little as possible after mixing in ice water.

title: yogurt shake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Mix at high speed for about 30 seconds.
Makes 1 shake.
Serve immediately to avoid separation.

title: lemon torte
directions: Mix together all ingredients and then press into a 9 x 12 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° or 20 minutes.
Do not over bake, should be a light golden brown.
Cool.

title: bacon hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into 4 pieces.
Cut bacon in half.
Wrap bacon around hot dogs and secure with a toothpick.
Put in a baking dish with toothpicks pointing up.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour or until bacon is crisp at 350°.
Let these cool a few minutes before serving.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Cream until smooth cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Put cupcake liners in cupcake tins.
Place vanilla wafer in each liner.
Fill about 3/4 full of cream cheese filling.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Top with your favorite pie filling: cherry, blueberry, etc.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Prepare grits as directed.
To cooked grits, add balance of ingredients and stir.
Pour into a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup grated Swiss cheese and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until browned slightly and set.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and shred potatoes in buttered dish.
Grate Cheddar cheese and combine with mustard, coffee cream, salt, milk and nutmeg. Heat.
Pour over potatoes and stir lightly; chill overnight.
Bake, uncovered at 325° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until lemon colored.
Add remaining dry ingredients until all are mixed well. Stir in zucchini.
Bake in oiled and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Test with toothpicks.

title: green party salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk in top of a double boiler.
Pour hot mixture over lime jello, stirring until dissolved.
Stir in cream cheese.
When cheese is dissolved, add pineapple.
Cool.
Blend in Cool Whip, mayonnaise and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Combine popcorn, peanuts, brown sugar, Karo syrup and butter. Mix vanilla, soda and vinegar and pour over your popped corn. Spread on cookie sheet and cook 1 hour at 250°.
Allow to cool and place in tight jar.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute onion, garlic, mushrooms and pepper.
Add the beans, tomatoes and spices.
Simmer gently for about 30 minutes.
Mix Cheddar cheese and yogurt.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, place a layer of sauce, 1 1/2 tablespoons of grated Mozzarella cheese and 4 tablespoons of cheese-yogurt mixture.
Repeat until all ingredients are used, ending with a layer of sauce.
Top with cheese-yogurt mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ham quiche
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk.
Mix until blended. Add ham, Swiss cheese and chives.
Pour into pastry lined 9-inch deep dish pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Use approximately 2 tablespoons per cup of boiling water.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Chop walnuts into medium-sized pieces.
Beat eggs; beat in sugar.
Then add oil and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to the first mixture, alternating with zucchini.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Divide mixture into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 2-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes or until done. The loaves freeze well.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put layers of potatoes and onion in greased baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant; cut up in cubes and place in saucepan with water.
Cook until soft; drain and mash with fork.
Set aside.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Mix eggs.
Mix 7-Up, lemon juice and flour.

title: special diet cake(for kids with special needs)
directions: Mix together all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into a 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: autumn pumpkin pie
directions: Beat with rotary beater until well blended. Pour into 9-inch pastry lined pie pan; bake 50 to 55 minutes at 375°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press raw meat on the bottom of an 8 x 11 inch casserole dish.
Spread soup, cheese and onions on top (onions last).
Put the tater tots on top of that and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until the meat is done.
Serve in squares.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients (except pecans).
Mix well and shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Roll ball into Handi-Wrap and place in fridge.
Yields 1 (4-inch) cheese ball.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Prepare first 4 ingredients.
Combine.
Blend dressing ingredients in a small bowl and pour over all.
Toss and serve.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix salt, sugar, milk and margarine on stove.
Heat until it comes to a boil.
Take off stove and add cocoa, vanilla, coconut and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Set by spoonful on wax paper or foil until set.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix well.
Pour 1/2 the mixture in mold and let set in refrigerator.
Spread large carton sour cream on set jello mixture. Pour on rest of jello mixture and keep in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: don't peek chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Mix 1st eleven ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour in baking pan.
Press chicken into mixture.
Sprinkle top with paprika. Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake for 2 1/2 hours.
Do not open cover (not even to peek) during baking.

title: fudge ecstasies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a heavy medium saucepan, heat half the chocolate pieces, the unsweetened chocolate and margarine or butter until melted, stirring occasionally.
Add eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla and baking powder.
Beat until thoroughly combined. Stir in the remaining chocolate pieces and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are firm and surfaces are dull and cracked.
Cool cookies on a wire rack.
Makes 36 pieces.

title: hershey chocolate cake
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: pork cabbage soup
directions: In 4 1/2-quart Dutch oven, brown pork cubes in hot cooking oil. Drain off excess fat.
Stir in rest of ingredients except sour cream.
Bring mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 40 minutes or until meat is tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Season to taste with additional salt and pepper.
Top each serving with a dollop of sour cream.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: ham strata - for breakfast
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer bread, meat and onion; top with eggs and milk.
Grate cheese on top.
Make the night before and refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Insert a knife to check for doneness.

title: hunter's beef
directions: Trim and discard fat from meat.
Cut into 4 to 6 serving size pieces.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
With a mallet, pound seasoned flour into meat.
Heat oil in a wide frying pan over medium-high heat.
Add meat; brown well on both sides.

title: chocolate finger cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sugar, butter and egg.
Blend well. Stir in flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder.
Chill dough (at least 1 hour).
Divide dough into 4 equal parts.
Shape each into roll 3/4-inches in diameter.
Place each roll 4-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
(Use 2 cookie sheets.)
With fork dipped in flour, flatten each roll to 1/4-inch thickness.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Boil cauliflower in the water until soft.
Allow to cool slightly.
Put cauliflower and 1 cup of the water in blender; blend until smooth.
Return blended mixture to pan with remaining water.
Add everything but cheese; boil, then add cheese.
Cook until melted.
Serve.

title: german string beans and bacon
directions: Cook string beans; reserve bean water and set aside.
Brown onion and bacon together.
Add approximately 2 tablespoons of Wondra flour to bacon and onion mixture.
Add some reserved string bean water until mixture is a smooth consistency.
Add 1/4 cup apple cider vinegar.
Stir in fresh ground pepper to taste. Add string beans.
Let simmer 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Will become thick.
Add a little water if too thick.
Cooking time:
1/2 hour.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Cover bottom of 11 x 15-inch pan with graham cracker crust made from last 3 ingredients.
Save 1 cup crumbs.
Slice bananas crosswise over crust.
Slice ice cream in 1/2-inch slices and place over bananas.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over ice cream.
Freeze until firm.

title: chewy walnut squares
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Stir the egg, brown sugar and vanilla together.
Quickly stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Add walnuts.
Spread in pan and bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes. Leave in pan.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16.

title: sausage and cream cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage in pan and drain all fat.
Add softened cream cheese to the browned sausage and stir until cream cheese is melted.
Add Rotele tomatoes and stir until well blended.
Serve warm with corn chips.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on the package, then drain, saving 1/2 cup of the water.
Brown onion and sausage.
Place noodles, sausage and onions in a large casserole dish.

title: microwave almond bark
directions: Melt semi-sweet chocolate pieces in microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes until shiny.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in 1 cup almonds; set aside.
Melt white chocolate bars in microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes until shiny.
Stir in 1 cup almonds; set aside.
Alternately spoon dollops of each mixture, side by side, onto waxed paper-lined cookie sheet, forming a thick layer of chocolate.
With knife, cut and twist to create a marbleized effect.
Top with sugar crystals.
Refrigerate until firm.
Break into pieces.
Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: miniature party pizzas
directions: In skillet, brown beef and sausage; drain well.
Add Cheez Whiz, stirring until melted.
Stir in garlic powder and Worcestershire.
Cool and spread on slices of rye bread.
Line up on cookie sheets and freeze until topping hardens.
Store in Ziploc bags.
Bake frozen pizzas at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen pizzas.

title: the best brownies
directions: Blend oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 60 minutes, or until brownies pull away from sides, at 325°.

title: cabbage rolls(german and polish dish)
directions: Place cabbage in boiling water and cook until leaves are softened and easy to separate.
Remove leaves individually from cabbage head.
Shred carrots; line bottom of casserole with 1/2 of carrots.

title: tutti-frutti lemon
directions: In large bowl, combine undrained pineapple, undrained orange sections and undrained fruit cocktail with flaked coconut and lemon juice.
Sprinkle dry lemon pudding mix over fruits and toss lightly to combine.
Chill.
Just before serving, peel bananas and slice to make 1 1/2 cups of bananas.
Fold bananas into lemon-fruit mixture; add nuts.
Serve in dessert dishes or sherbet glasses.
Top with whipped topping.
Makes 10 servings.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Chunk potatoes.
Boil and drain.
Mix all ingredients together in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour the dressing over.
Let set overnight for best results.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook the sweet potatoes just long enough to be tender; peel, then cut crosswise and lengthwise to form chunks. Let cool. Put into a 2-quart casserole dish or pan; dot with butter. Mix together the corn syrup, maple flavoring and bourbon, if used; pour over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Garnish with parsley.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Melt margarine.
Add other ingredients.
Cook until thick on medium-low heat.
Cool completely.
Fold in a small carton of Cool Whip.

title: duchess potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or microwave for 4 to 5 minutes.
May also add chopped, drained pimento and/or Cheddar cheese.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Melt chocolate bits and butter.
Stir until smooth; cool slightly and spread on top of other frosting.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Batter will be very stiff.
Pat in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fig preserve cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, soda and spices.
Gradually add oil and beat well.
Add figs, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Pour sauce over cake while still warm.

title: goodie bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, melted butter or margarine and 1 egg. Spread in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts over top of cake mix layer.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 2 eggs together.
Spread on top of nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: horchata(spanish almond milkshake)
directions: Combine ingredients in a blender and blend until well mixed. Serve immediately.

title: mexican salad
directions: Just before serving, break and crush taco chips.
Toss with a mixture of all ingredients, except dressing.
Then add enough dressing to moisten.
Toss and serve immediately.

title: delicious caramel
