directions: Place unopened can in a pan of boiling water to cover can. Boil for three hours, making sure can remains covered with water. Remove from heat and drain off water and let can cool for an hour or so.
Refrigerate.

title: toasty cheese bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Toast bread; butter both sides.
Cook and stir meat, onion, celery, prepared mustard and 1/2 teaspoon salt until the meat is brown and onion is tender.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in Bundt pan at 350° or in glass pan at 325°.

title: cherry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs.
Add baking soda to sour milk, then stir flour, spices and milk alternately into creamed mixture.
Simmer cherries on stove and sweeten to taste.
Cool cherries; drain.
Add cherries, vanilla and nuts to creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: new england brown bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine all-purpose flour, baking soda and salt.
In another bowl, combine whole wheat flour, buttermilk and molasses.
Add to first flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into two well-greased coffee cans (5 1/4 x 3 3/4-inch).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat chocolate and shortening in 3-quart saucepan over low heat until melted.
Stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan, about 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: belgian stew
directions: Brown and drain the beef cubes.
Add brown sugar and caramelize into meat.
Add 2 cups water, beef cubes, bay leaves, garlic (crushed) and shallots.
Simmer for 2 hours, stirring frequently and never allowing to loose level of liquid.
Thicken to desired consistency with cornstarch.
Serve with boiled potatoes and carrots.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion in small amount of oleo.
Cook broccoli and drain. Mix the Cheez Whiz and soup; heat.
Mix all together rice, broccoli, onion and soup mixture.
Pour into a baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Heat in oven for a few minutes.

title: double layer fudge
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, mix sugar, butter, marshmallow cream and Pet milk. Cook and stir until a full rolling boil. Stir over medium heat 5 minutes. Take off heat and pour half of mixture into a heatproof bowl. To one half, add chocolate chips; to the other half, add caramel or butterscotch chips. Add nuts. Beat one half until chips are melted. Spread in a
well buttered dish. Beat the other half and spread over first batch. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: mexican corn and zucchini
directions: Cook and stir onion and garlic in butter in a 10-inch skillet until tender. Stir in corn and remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling, then reduce heat. Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pie crust flaky pastry
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening and butter.
Add water, sprinkling 1 tablespoon at a time, until pastry holds together to form a dough.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Let stand a few minutes before rolling.

title: bonnie's baked limas
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Mix remaining ingredients, except bacon.
Lay bacon strips over mixture; bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: pepper turkey loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine turkey with remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into a loaf and place on a rack in a shallow baking pan.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour.

title: "butterscotch delight"
directions: 1st Layer:
Crush pecan sandies cookies (finely) and mix with 1/2 to 1 stick melted butter.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Spread dough on cookie sheet; bake until golden brown and let cool.
Mix cream cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise; spread over dough.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Add all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: crab imperial(governor's mansion in annapolis, maryland)
directions: Remove all cartilage from crabmeat.
In medium size pan, melt margarine or butter.
Mix in flour.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly to keep mixture smooth and free from lumps.
Cook, stirring, over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Mix in onion, Worcestershire sauce and bread cubes. Cool.
Fold in mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.

title: cranberry conserve
directions: Wash cranberries and combine all ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until all cranberries have popped open (about 30 minutes).
Remove from heat and allow to cool. Fill containers and store in cool place.
Makes 6 (1/2 pint) jars.

title: mike's munchies
directions: Spread peanut butter on crackers.
Put marshmallows on top and bake in oven at 350° for about 3 to 5 minutes (or until marshmallows start to brown).

title: milk chocolate torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, chill frosting mix (dry) and whipping cream for 1 hour.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter into pan. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely.
Cut cake crosswise in half.
Blend frosting mix and cream; beat until stiff.
Fill layer with 1/2 the frosting mixture and almonds.
Top cake with the rest of frosting mixture and almonds.
Freeze at least 8 hours.
Cut into 3 x 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Serve with warm sauce.
Makes approximately 15 servings.

title: carnival pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare pastry mix and line a large (12-inch round) pie pan.
Cut up sausage meat and ground beef into small pieces.
Brown in a skillet.

title: cheater cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and milk together.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour pie filling onto mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Layer all ingredients in trifle dish.
Repeat layers, ending with Cool Whip.
It looks pretty!

title: zucchini soup
directions: Melt oleo and add zucchini.
Add onion, salt, pepper, water and bouillon.
Cook until tender.
In blender, blend zucchini to puree.
Serve hot in cream soup bowls; top with sour cream.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook bacon and onion until brown.
Add remaining ingredients. Place in baking dish.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs and brown in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate oatmeal drops
directions: Place sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in a large bowl and cook on High setting 2 minutes in microwave. Stir well and reduce heat setting to Medium. Cook for 3 to 4 minutes until mixture starts to boil. Blend in vanilla, salt and peanut butter. Add oatmeal and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper; chill until firm.

title: beef brisket
directions: Line bottom of casserole or Dutch oven with celery and onions. Lay brisket on top of vegetables and bay leaf on top of meat.

title: apple banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Then add eggs and fruit. Mix in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured loaf pans (8 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour or when bread tests done.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken in saltwater until done and debone chicken. Save broth. Boil broth and chicken soup and pour over deboned chicken in a baking dish.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix in order given and pour into greased 12 3/4 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: gingerbread cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter and flour a 1 1/2-quart ovenproof glass or metal loaf pan. Mix together cake mix, water, bourbon, eggs and melted butter. Beat for 30 seconds. Pour batter into greased pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool completely before removing from pan.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into a casserole dish.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together and add eggs, beating well. Add this, milk and red food coloring to the creamed sugar and shortening.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: yum yum cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour cookie sheet. Spread dough on greased cookie sheet.

title: slush
directions: Stir ingredients together and freeze overnight.

title: skillet pot roast with vegetables(football sunday dinner)
directions: In a large skillet, brown roast in hot fat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Put in large Dutch oven.
Add water to partially cover meat.
Cover pot tightly.
Simmer for 1 hour, adding water when necessary.

title: macaroni and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well. Cook macaroni as directed on package, drain well. Combine sausage and macaroni in a sprayed casserole dish. Slightly beat egg and mix with soup. Combine with macaroni and sausage. Sprinkle crumbs on top and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: moravian christmas cookies
directions: Helpful Hints:
Cover your board to roll your cookies on. Cover your rolling pin with a rolling pin sock.
This helps keep the dough from sticking.
This yields 7 pounds cookies.

title: low-fat lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Mix spaghetti sauce and water.
In another bowl, combine the cottage cheese, egg substitute, garlic powder and pepper.

Coat the bottom of the baking dish with some of the sauce, then place a layer of hard (uncooked) lasagne noodles on top. Cover noodles with another layer of sauce, then spoon 1/2 the cheese mixture over the sauce. Repeat with a layer of noodles, then sauce, then cheese mixture.
Finally add the remaining sauce, making sure that the noodles are completely covered.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 50 minutes. Sprinkle some grated Mozzarella cheese over the top during the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: delicious chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken in bottom of a large oblong Pyrex dish (baking). Heat celery soup (no water), 1/2 stick butter and 1 cup chicken broth together.
Pour over cubed chicken; add 1 package frozen vegetables (cauliflower, broccoli and carrot mixture).
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Will be thin.
Pour over all.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Stir together; add 2 cups boiling water.
Then cook 5 minutes, or until very clear.
Cool mixture.
Put berries in pie shell; pour glaze over and refrigerate.
Top with whipped Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: chocolate mousse cake
directions: Butter bottom and sides of spring-form pan.
Melt chips and water; set aside.
Beat sugar and egg yolks, melted chocolate, salt and cream of tartar.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Arrange ladyfingers or cookies around side of pan, standing upright.
Crumble remainder on bottom of pan.
Add mousse.
Chill.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients with mixer until well blended.
Store in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Slice fruit:
oranges, pineapple, grapes, pears, strawberries, plums, etc.
Makes great appetizer.

title: squash ritz
directions: Boil squash; drain and add butter.
Beat egg and add to squash.
Add onion, salt and pepper, then crackers.
Pour into a 2-quart Pyrex casserole and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: my mom's cookies
directions: Boil mixture of margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Let boil for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
The mixture will thicken up.
Add in the peanut butter and oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Allow time for cookies to set, approximately 30 minutes.

title: lemonade dream pie
directions: Use half Cool Whip. Mix frozen lemonade, Eagle Brand and Cool Whip in bowl. Place mixture in pie crust. Chill 1 hour. Cover pie mixture with remaining Cool Whip. Serve cold.

title: hoe cake
directions: Mix together.
Add enough water to make mixture almost soupy. Have black iron skillet greased with bacon drippings and spattering hot.
Pour mixture in pan cook on medium heat until brown, then turn over and cook until done.
Serves 4-6.

title: virgin island authentic cruzan recipes
directions: Cook wings and first 6 ingredients over a low flame until tender.
Add 1 quart water, potatoes and rice.
Bring to a boil and then turn heat to low until rice is soft.
Can also be made with leftover meats and fish instead of wings.

title: crab salad
directions: Chop up crab, onion and celery. Add mayo, as much as to your liking, mix well and chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Mix beans and taco seasoning.
Layer in bottom of dish.
Peel and seed avocado, then mash it.
Blend in lemon juice and sour cream until smooth.
Layer on top of bean mixture, then a layer each of the remaining ingredients in order as listed.

title: chocolate diamonds
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over hot water.
Add remaining ingredients except nuts.
Mix well.
Spread in 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: cantaloupe alaska
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar to soft peaks.
Beat in dry milk and sugar.
Beat to stiff peaks.
Place cantaloupe slices on cookie sheet.
Top each with a scoop of ice cream.
Cover with meringue, covering each cantaloupe slice and ice cream completely. Bake 5 minutes at 500° or until lightly browned.

title: steak and potato supper
directions: Roll steak in flour.
Fry in oil until browned.
Place meat in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, no excess fat.
Scrape up brown drippings in pan.
Add to meat.
Arrange potatoes, onion and parsley in pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomato sauce. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: easy fix punch
directions: Simply mix together and enjoy!

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add almond extract.
Stir in the flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Turn mixture into the pan.
Spoon pie filling into cake pan in 16 spots, spacing 4 spoonfuls evenly in each direction.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done. Filling will sink into cake while baking.

title: herbed shrimp soup
directions: Heat oil.
Add the onion and cook until softened, about 3 minutes.
Add the tomatoes and jalapenos; cook 3 minutes longer. Add clam juice, chicken broth and marjoram.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add the shrimp and simmer about 5 minutes, until they are pink, loosely curled and opaque.

title: cabbage and dumplings
directions: Chop cabbage.
Saute with oil and salt for about 30 minutes. Make dough as directed below and mix with cabbage.
(Shell macaroni may be substituted for dumplings.)

title: catfish pickles
directions: Combine tomatoes, onions and bell pepper.
Stir in pickling salt and let set overnight.
Rinse with clear water and drain well.
Make syrup.

title: crispy caramel treats
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan on low heat. Add marshmallows. Stir until melted smooth. Remove from heat. Add broken pretzel sticks; mix lightly until well coated. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheet. Melt caramels with water in heavy saucepan on low heat, stirring frequently. Add peanut butter; mix well. Drizzle over treats. Cool.

title: cherry nut cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening egg, vanilla and milk.
Add cherries, walnuts and flour.
Bake at 375 degrees 12 - 15 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: To corn, add sugar and salt; stir well.
Mix the beaten eggs and milk together.
Pour mixture into the corn.
Add the melted butter.
Mix thoroughly and spoon the mixture into a well buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Set the casserole into a pan of hot water and set this into a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes until set.
Test inserting a clean knife into the center of the pudding.
If it comes out clean, it's done.

title: spicy cuban beef
directions: Cut beef into 1 1/2-inch cubes (or you may substitute an equivalent amount of ground beef).
Spray a large, nonstick skillet or heavy Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Add beef; brown over high heat.
Turn frequently to prevent sticking.
Drain fat, if any, from pan.
Add remaining ingredients, except olives and rice. Cover and simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Uncover; simmer until nearly all liquid evaporates.
Stir in olives and heat through.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: cantaloupe frost
directions: In a blender, combine milk and melon.
Blend until smooth. Add yogurt and blend.
Serves 4.

title: crab puffs supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine first 5 ingredients in medium bowl and mix well.
Combine water, butter and salt in large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and immediately add flour, beating until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms ball.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Thoroughly blend in crab mixture.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes more.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: bread
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Heat water.
Add sugar; dissolve. Add oil and Starter to sugar mixture.
Add liquid to flour mixture; stir into dough.
Knead lightly.
Return to oiled bowl. Let rise in a warm place overnight.
In the morning, punch down; knead 1 minute.
Divide into 3 loaf pans (oiled).
Oil top. Cover; let rise until approximately 4 p.m.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: one pan blueberry cobbler
directions: The batter rises to the top as it bakes, forming a cake like crust.

title: macaroni and cheese salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Rinse with cold water; drain well. Add next 5 ingredients and mix well; chill.
Just before serving, fold in next 3 ingredients.
Season to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: nut bread
directions: Soak nuts and raisins in bourbon for 2 hours.
Drain, saving liquid for cake.
Cream butter and 1/2 the sugar well; add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add flour and bourbon, rotating.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Mix in nuts and raisins.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add the other 1/2 sugar.
Fold into dough.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: easy shrimp dip
directions: Rinse shrimp and drain well. Mash 1/2 of the shrimp with a fork. Mix with French onion dip. Fold in the rest of whole shrimp. Chill.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt mixture.
Mix together egg, vinegar and water.
Add to flour mixture.
Chill in refrigerator for short while.
Roll out.
Makes 3 pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Stir and bring to a boil the water and sugar.
Add flavoring. Vanilla and maple are the easiest to find.
But you can use any flavoring that you like. This will keep in the refrigerator in a covered jar.

title: sandra's blackened catfish
directions: Use pond-raised catfish fillets.
I personally like the 3 to 5-ounce size, if you have a choice.
My son, John, buys them from one of the ponds in Mississippi in a 15-pound box and I keep them in the freezer.
Take out the number of fillets you think you will need and thaw in cold water.
When thawed, drain water off fish and pat lightly with paper towels.
Don't get them too dry or they won't hold the batter well.
Mix the amount of white cornmeal you think you will need with salt and black or red pepper to taste.
I sometimes put just a sprinkling of garlic powder in, too.
Dredge fish in this mixture on both sides, making sure the whole surface is well covered.
Lay on a cookie sheet, in layers, with paper towels between each layer.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to cook.

title: apricot slush
directions: Mix together and freeze in cube trays.
To serve, fill glass 3/4 full of frozen cubes, fill with 7-Up or Squirt.
Mix and serve.

title: apple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cheddar cheese and parsley. Microwave for 2 to 4 minutes on 50% power to blend flavors.
Add Cheddar cheese and chill.
After chilling, form ball and roll in chopped parsley.
(May use dry parsley.)
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo and Crisco.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla. Add coconut and chopped nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta florentine
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix spinach, Mozzarella cheese, egg white, Parmesan cheese and nutmeg until blended.
Fill each pasta shell with a heaping tablespoonful of spinach mixture.
Place in greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spoon sauce over shells.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 servings.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast cake in 1 cup of warm water.
Mix as for biscuits.
Roll and cut out.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 425°.

title: navajo fry bread
directions: Stir together flour, milk powder, baking powder, and salt. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in water to make dough soft.
Turn out onto floured surface.
Knead to smooth ball.
Divide into eight balls.
Cover and let rest ten minutes.
Turn out onto floured surfaces.
Roll each ball into six inch circles.
Fry one at a time in deep, hot, cooking oil until golden brown, turning once.
Drain and serve hot.

title: salmon log
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans and parsley, into salmon and chill for several hours for better handling.
Then roll in chopped pecans and chopped parsley.
Serve as spread for crackers.

title: creamy broccoli casserole
directions: Slice and cook broccoli; drain and set aside.
Blend together the soup, mayonnaise, water chestnuts and curry powder.
Place broccoli
in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Squeeze lemon juice over top and cover with soup mix.
Can top with breading and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in large bowl that can withstand heat. Mix sugar and milk in a large saucepan.
Bring to a simmer at moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to just maintain that simmer and continue to cook for 8 minutes, stirring constantly as mixture scorches easily.
Add sugar and milk mixture to first 3 ingredients; stir quickly until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch dish and refrigerate to cool and harden. Remove from refrigerator about 15 minutes before cutting for easier cutting.
May add one cup of any type of nuts when vanilla is added, if desired.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: After cake cools, cut into squares.
Mix pudding in another container.
In a trifle bowl, layer as follows twice:
cake, pudding, Cool Whip and grated candy.
Layer twice, then sprinkle extra candy on top.

title: giant pretzel
directions: Mix water, yeast and sugar.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Place salt and flour in a bowl.
Add yeast mixture and stir.
Shape into desired shape.
Beat egg and brush on top.
Bake 12 minutes at 425°.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups crushed pretzels, butter and sugar together. Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt oleo in large pan; add brown sugar.
Mix well.
Cool about 5 minutes.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add nuts and chocolate chips; mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: italian pork chops
directions: Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dredge pork chops in crumbs, then in egg and again in crumb mixture.
Place in Pyrex dish that has 1/4 cup melted butter in it.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Turn after 30 minutes.
Recipe works well for boneless chicken.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Layer 2 cans of Frito-Lay bean dip on a platter.
Top with mashed avocados with lemon juice and pepper.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix ingredients together in crock-pot.
Cook for 2 to 3 hours on low.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices; set aside. Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl, mix well. Add flour mixture, stirring well.
Stir in apples.
Spoon into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cherry squares
directions: Combine butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and flour, then vanilla and lemon juice; blend well.
Spread into a 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet.
Drop spoonfuls of filling on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top. Cut into squares.

title: custard rice pudding
directions: Wash and drain rice and add to milk and cook covered for 15 to 20 minutes until tender.
Beat egg yolks thoroughly.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar and the salt.
Mix in some hot rice mixture and then add to remaining rice mixture.
Cook, stirring for 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Cool.
Add sherry.
Beat egg whites until foamy and add remaining 3 tablespoons sugar.
Beat until stiff. Add to rice mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; salt to taste and mash.
Mix carrots, onions, soup, pimentos, sour cream and margarine to cooked squash.
Add 1/2 package of stuffing mix.
Pour into greased baking dish and top with remaining poultry stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Can be divided into 2 casserole dishes.
Freezes well!

title: creamy french frosting
directions: Mix confectioners sugar, egg and Crisco together in a bowl. Bring to a boil 3/8 cup sugar and water.
Pour over mixture in the bowl and beat.

title: hidden valley ranch spinach dip
directions: Combine ingredients, blending well.
Chill one hour, then get 1 round loaf white or French bread and hollow out the middle. Put dip in and with the parts you cut out make bread cubes for dipping.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, salt and pumpkin pie mix. Add milk last.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: pot-lucky tuna
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and celery; cook until lightly browned.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper to form smooth paste.
Gradually add milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Add cheese, tuna and vegetables; pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with biscuits and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexi-chili casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet; add onion and cook about 5 minutes. Drain off fat.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Add tomato sauce and beans.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crushed corn chips and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: mama's snickerdoodles
directions: Grease	cookie	sheet.	Cream the butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar until it is
light	and
fluffy.
Add
eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift the
flour,
cream
of	tartar, soda and salt together.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Combine cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar;	roll balls
of dough into mixture to coat. Mash with fingers (this
makes
them
pretty) or with a glass. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: ginger pickles
directions: Bring to a boil and pour
over pickles; let stand 3 days. Drain solution.
Add 1 cup sugar; reheat
and pour onto pickles. Let stand 3 days.
Repeat until 3 cups
sugar
have
been
added. Pack pickles into jars.
Heat vinegar solution.
Pour
over pickles and seal.
(Will also keep without sealing.)

title: lowered cholesterol egg salad
directions: Set eggs in medium saucepan. Cover with water. Heat to a boil. Let boil for 5 minutes. Let eggs cool and remove shells. Remove 3 of the yolks and throw away. Take a fork and gently shred the remaining 3 whole eggs and 3 egg whites. Add the mayonnaise, onion and celery; mix, then add pepper and mustard to taste. Spread on slices of bread. Garnish with tomato and lettuce. Serves 4 sandwiches.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: Sprinkle steak with paprika and allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.
Cook steak and garlic in butter until meat is browned.
Add onions and green peppers; continue cooking until vegetables wilt.
Add tomatoes and broth.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes.
Blend water with cornstarch and soy sauce.
Stir into steak and cook until thickened.
Serve over beds of fluffy rice. Serves 6.

title: apple oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients well, then sift together.
Set aside. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add oats and fruit.
Mix on low speed.
Add sifted dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix well with a spoon.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Yields approximately 4 dozen.

title: california mix
directions: Cook vegetables; combine.
Make cheese sauce by combining flour and butter or margarine in small saucepan.
Stir until margarine melts; add milk.
Continue stirring until milk is hot and sauce is thick; add cheese.
Melt and pour over vegetables.

title: barbecue bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Combine other ingredients, except cheese and biscuits.
Add hamburger (drained) and mix well.
Pour in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cut biscuits in half and put on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix everything together.
Chill.
Make into 2 large balls and roll in the nuts.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and tinfoil.
Freeze or chill until used.
Great with any kind of crackers.

title: gingerbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9-inch square cake pan. Mix all ingredients with mixer at low speed; beat until well mixed.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Place flour in a plastic bag.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time; shake until well coated.
In large skillet over medium heat, brown a few pieces of chicken at a time in oil.
Transfer to a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, skin side up.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; set aside.
Drain pineapple juice into a 2-cup measuring cup.
Add water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid; reserve liquid and pineapple slices.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Flour raisins and nuts.
Add to mixture.
Bake in 4 layers at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: wine jello
directions: Mix well in bowl the gelatin and sugar; add boiling water. Stir until dissolved. Add juice and wine. Mold and chill.
Serve as dessert or as accompaniment to poultry.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrot in food processor.

title: steak sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Use liberally.
Broil, as usual. Brush on sauce while cooking.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Use glass or Corning Ware container.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Melt butter and add cubes; toss to cover cubes well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate and butter on top of double boiler.
Beat in sugar.
Fold in flour and salt.
Add vanilla.
Beat eggs and fold into mixture.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs in vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with water to egg mixture.
Stir in sauerkraut.
Put in greased pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: heavenly cheesecake brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed on package. Pour into greased 13 x 9 pan that was sprayed. Beat cream cheese until smooth. Add sugar, egg and vanilla. Pour cream cheese mixture over brownie mixture; cut through batter with knife several times for marbled effect. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool. Makes 24 brownies.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Serve with crackers or veggies.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, butter and water on medium speed for 4 minutes.
Add bananas and pecans.
Put into 2 loaf pans and cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: beef stew
directions: In 2 tablespoons oil, brown meat after dipping in flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Add chopped onion and stir in Dutch oven for 5 minutes.
Add canned broth and marjoram.
Add cut carrots, celery and potatoes and 2 cups water; cook on medium high heat until vegetables are tender, about 45 minutes.
Serve.
Great reheated, too!

title: german steak tarare
directions: Mix beef with beaten egg.
Add chopped onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately on buttered ry bread.

title: strawberry layer dessert
directions: Drain strawberries, reserving 1/2 cup syrup. Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add reserved syrup. Chill until partially set. Beat mixture until light and fluffy. Fold in whipped cream. Chill until of spreading consistency. Transfer 1 1/2 cups of mixture to small bowl. Fold in drained strawberries. Split cake crosswise, making 3 equal layers. Fill between layers with strawberry mixture. Frost top and sides of cake with remaining whipped cream mixture. Chill until serving time. Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add bananas and mix until smooth.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture, stirring just enough to moisten.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to complete cooling.

title: cheryl's chicken
directions: Cook and cut chicken into pieces.
Layer chicken in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with a layer of Swiss cheese slices. Mix the soup with milk and pour over the cheese and chicken.
Melt margarine and add stuffing.
Mix together and cover top of chicken and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mystery cream cheese pecan pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to package directions for a one crust (9-inch) filled pie.
Refrigerate remaining crust for later use.
In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, granulated sugar, 1 of the eggs, 1 teaspoon vanilla and salt until smooth.
Pour over bottom of prepared crust.
Sprinkle pecans over cream cheese layer.

title: neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients; batter will be stiff.
Using your fingers, pat the batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan; set aside.

title: double apple muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients, except apples, mixing just until moistened.
Gently fold in apples.
Fill cups 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 1 dozen.
One muffin = 160 calories and contains 24 gr. carbohydrates, 3 gr. protein and 6 gr. fat.

title: cranberry almond bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms of two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.

title: jerky marinade
directions: Slice meat thin ( a meat slicer works well).
Put all jalapeno juice in and cut up a few jalapenos, depending on how hot you want taste (optional).	Marinate for 3 to 4 days in juice mixture.
Place on trays of a food dehydrator and cook for 8 hours rotating trays every two hours, top to bottom.
This will do 5 pounds of meat, venison or beef.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars and pudding mix in large mixer bowl.
Blend until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs.

title: chili sauce
directions: Grind the first 3 ingredients. Put in a large pot. Add remaining ingredients. Boil slowly for 3 hours, uncovered. Pour into sterilized jars and seal tightly. Great with meat loaf or any meat dishes. Makes about 5 1/2 pints. Green tomatoes can be used.

title: cockeyed cake
directions: Spray 9 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Sift dry ingredients directly into the pan.
Mix lightly with wooden spoon and make three hollows in flour mixture.
Mix melted butter, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour into hollows.
Pour 1 cup cold water over everything and stir just until mixed with wooden spoon.
Frost by sprinkling batter with 1/2 cup chocolate chips and pecan halves.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
